2516struct PhiOp : OperationT<PhiOp> {
2517 RegisterRepresentation rep;
2518
2519 // Phis have to remain at the beginning of the current block. As effects
2520 // cannot express this completely, we just mark them as having no effects but
2521 // treat them specially when scheduling operations.
2522 static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects();
2523 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
2524 return base::VectorOf(&rep, 1);
2525 }
2526
2527 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
2528 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
2529 storage.resize(input_count);
2530 for (size_t i = 0; i < input_count; ++i) {
2531 storage[i] = rep;
2532 }
2533 return base::VectorOf(storage);
2534 }
2535
2536 static constexpr size_t kLoopPhiBackEdgeIndex = 1;
2537
2538 explicit PhiOp(base::Vector<const OpIndex> inputs, RegisterRepresentation rep)
2539 : Base(inputs), rep(rep) {}
2540
2541 template <typename Fn, typename Mapper>
2542 V8_INLINE auto Explode(Fn fn, Mapper& mapper) const {
2543 auto mapped_inputs = mapper.template Map<64>(inputs());
2544 return fn(base::VectorOf(mapped_inputs), rep);
2545 }
2546
2547 void Validate(const Graph& graph) const { DCHECK_GT(input_count, 0); }
2548 auto options() const { return std::tuple{rep}; }
2549};
2550
2551// Used as a placeholder for a loop-phi while building the graph, replaced with
2552// a normal `PhiOp` before graph building is over, so it should never appear in
2553// a complete graph.
2554struct PendingLoopPhiOp : FixedArityOperationT<1, PendingLoopPhiOp> {
2555 RegisterRepresentation rep;
2556
2557 static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects();
2558 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
2559 return base::VectorOf(&rep, 1);
2560 }
2561
2562 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
2563 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
2564 return InputsRepFactory::SingleRep(rep);
2565 }
2566
2567 OpIndex first() const { return input(0); }
2568 PendingLoopPhiOp(OpIndex first, RegisterRepresentation rep)
2569 : Base(first), rep(rep) {}
2570
2571 auto options() const { return std::tuple{rep}; }
2572};
2573
2574struct ConstantOp : FixedArityOperationT<0, ConstantOp> {
2575 enum class Kind : uint8_t {
2576 kWord32,
2577 kWord64,
2578 kFloat32,
2579 kFloat64,
2580 kSmi,
2581 kNumber, // TODO(tebbi): See if we can avoid number constants.
2582 kTaggedIndex,
2583 kExternal,
2584 kHeapObject,
2585 kCompressedHeapObject,
2586 kTrustedHeapObject,
2587 kRelocatableWasmCall,
2588 kRelocatableWasmStubCall,
2589 kRelocatableWasmIndirectCallTarget,
2590 kRelocatableWasmCanonicalSignatureId
2591 };
2592
2593 Kind kind;
2594 RegisterRepresentation rep = Representation(kind);
2595 union Storage {
2596 uint64_t integral;
2597 i::Float32 float32;
2598 i::Float64 float64;
2599 ExternalReference external;
2600 IndirectHandle<HeapObject> handle;
2601
2602 Storage(uint64_t integral = 0) : integral(integral) {}
2603 Storage(i::Tagged<Smi> smi) : integral(smi.ptr()) {}
2604 Storage(i::Float64 constant) : float64(constant) {}
2605 Storage(i::Float32 constant) : float32(constant) {}
2606 Storage(ExternalReference constant) : external(constant) {}
2607 Storage(IndirectHandle<HeapObject> constant) : handle(constant) {}
2608
2609 inline bool operator==(const ConstantOp::Storage&) const {
2610 // It is tricky to implement this properly. We currently need to define
2611 // this for the matchers, but this should never be called.
2612 UNREACHABLE();
2613 }
2614 } storage;
2615
2616 static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects();
2617 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
2618 return base::VectorOf(&rep, 1);
2619 }
2620
2621 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
2622 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>&) const {
2623 return {};
2624 }
2625
2626 static RegisterRepresentation Representation(Kind kind) {
2627 switch (kind) {
2628 case Kind::kRelocatableWasmCanonicalSignatureId:
2629 case Kind::kWord32:
2630 return RegisterRepresentation::Word32();
2631 case Kind::kWord64:
2632 return RegisterRepresentation::Word64();
2633 case Kind::kFloat32:
2634 return RegisterRepresentation::Float32();
2635 case Kind::kFloat64:
2636 return RegisterRepresentation::Float64();
2637 case Kind::kExternal:
2638 case Kind::kTaggedIndex:
2639 case Kind::kTrustedHeapObject:
2640 case Kind::kRelocatableWasmCall:
2641 case Kind::kRelocatableWasmStubCall:
2642 return RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr();
2643 case Kind::kRelocatableWasmIndirectCallTarget:
2644 return RegisterRepresentation::Word32();
2645 case Kind::kSmi:
2646 case Kind::kHeapObject:
2647 case Kind::kNumber:
2648 return RegisterRepresentation::Tagged();
2649 case Kind::kCompressedHeapObject:
2650 return RegisterRepresentation::Compressed();
2651 }
2652 }
2653
2654 ConstantOp(Kind kind, Storage storage)
2655 : Base(), kind(kind), storage(storage) {}
2656
2657 void Validate(const Graph& graph) const {
2658 DCHECK_IMPLIES(
2659 kind == Kind::kWord32,
2660 storage.integral <= WordRepresentation::Word32().MaxUnsignedValue());
2661 DCHECK_IMPLIES(
2662 kind == Kind::kRelocatableWasmCanonicalSignatureId,
2663 storage.integral <= WordRepresentation::Word32().MaxSignedValue());
2664 }
2665
2666 uint64_t integral() const {
2667 DCHECK(IsIntegral());
2668 return storage.integral;
2669 }
2670
2671 int64_t signed_integral() const {
2672 DCHECK(IsIntegral());
2673 switch (kind) {
2674 case Kind::kWord32:
2675 case Kind::kRelocatableWasmCanonicalSignatureId:
2676 return static_cast<int32_t>(storage.integral);
2677 case Kind::kWord64:
2678 return static_cast<int64_t>(storage.integral);
2679 default:
2680 UNREACHABLE();
2681 }
2682 }
2683
2684 uint32_t word32() const {
2685 DCHECK(kind == Kind::kWord32 || kind == Kind::kWord64);
2686 return static_cast<uint32_t>(storage.integral);
2687 }
2688
2689 uint64_t word64() const {
2690 DCHECK_EQ(kind, Kind::kWord64);
2691 return static_cast<uint64_t>(storage.integral);
2692 }
2693
2694 i::Tagged<Smi> smi() const {
2695 DCHECK_EQ(kind, Kind::kSmi);
2696 return i::Tagged<Smi>(storage.integral);
2697 }
2698
2699 i::Float64 number() const {
2700 DCHECK_EQ(kind, Kind::kNumber);
2701 return storage.float64;
2702 }
2703
2704 i::Float32 float32() const {
2705 DCHECK_EQ(kind, Kind::kFloat32);
2706 return storage.float32;
2707 }
2708
2709 i::Float64 float64() const {
2710 DCHECK_EQ(kind, Kind::kFloat64);
2711 return storage.float64;
2712 }
2713
2714 int32_t tagged_index() const {
2715 DCHECK_EQ(kind, Kind::kTaggedIndex);
2716 return static_cast<int32_t>(static_cast<uint32_t>(storage.integral));
2717 }
2718
2719 ExternalReference external_reference() const {
2720 DCHECK_EQ(kind, Kind::kExternal);
2721 return storage.external;
2722 }
2723
2724 IndirectHandle<i::HeapObject> handle() const {
2725 DCHECK(kind == Kind::kHeapObject || kind == Kind::kCompressedHeapObject ||
2726 kind == Kind::kTrustedHeapObject);
2727 return storage.handle;
2728 }
2729
2730 bool IsWord(uint64_t value) const {
2731 switch (kind) {
2732 case Kind::kWord32:
2733 return static_cast<uint32_t>(value) == word32();
2734 case Kind::kWord64:
2735 return value == word64();
2736 default:
2737 UNREACHABLE();
2738 }
2739 }
2740
2741 bool IsIntegral() const {
2742 return kind == Kind::kWord32 || kind == Kind::kWord64 ||
2743 kind == Kind::kRelocatableWasmCall ||
2744 kind == Kind::kRelocatableWasmStubCall ||
2745 kind == Kind::kRelocatableWasmCanonicalSignatureId ||
2746 kind == Kind::kRelocatableWasmIndirectCallTarget;
2747 }
2748
2749 auto options() const { return std::tuple{kind, storage}; }
2750
2751 void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;
2752 size_t hash_value(
2753 HashingStrategy strategy = HashingStrategy::kDefault) const {
2754 switch (kind) {
2755 case Kind::kWord32:
2756 case Kind::kWord64:
2757 case Kind::kSmi:
2758 case Kind::kTaggedIndex:
2759 case Kind::kRelocatableWasmCall:
2760 case Kind::kRelocatableWasmStubCall:
2761 case Kind::kRelocatableWasmIndirectCallTarget:
2762 case Kind::kRelocatableWasmCanonicalSignatureId:
2763 return HashWithOptions(storage.integral);
2764 case Kind::kFloat32:
2765 return HashWithOptions(storage.float32.get_bits());
2766 case Kind::kFloat64:
2767 case Kind::kNumber:
2768 return HashWithOptions(storage.float64.get_bits());
2769 case Kind::kExternal:
2770 return HashWithOptions(strategy == HashingStrategy::kMakeSnapshotStable
2771 ? 0
2772 : storage.external.raw());
2773 case Kind::kHeapObject:
2774 case Kind::kCompressedHeapObject:
2775 case Kind::kTrustedHeapObject:
2776 if (strategy == HashingStrategy::kMakeSnapshotStable) {
2777 return HashWithOptions();
2778 }
2779 return HashWithOptions(storage.handle.address());
2780 }
2781 }
2782 bool operator==(const ConstantOp& other) const {
2783 if (kind != other.kind) return false;
2784 switch (kind) {
2785 case Kind::kWord32:
2786 case Kind::kWord64:
2787 case Kind::kSmi:
2788 case Kind::kTaggedIndex:
2789 case Kind::kRelocatableWasmCall:
2790 case Kind::kRelocatableWasmStubCall:
2791 case Kind::kRelocatableWasmCanonicalSignatureId:
2792 case Kind::kRelocatableWasmIndirectCallTarget:
2793 return storage.integral == other.storage.integral;
2794 case Kind::kFloat32:
2795 // Using a bit_cast to uint32_t in order to return false when comparing
2796 // +0 and -0.
2797 // Note: for JavaScript, it would be fine to return true when both
2798 // values are NaNs, but for Wasm we must not merge NaNs that way.
2799 // Since we canonicalize NaNs for JS anyway, we don't need to treat
2800 // them specially here.
2801 return base::bit_cast<uint32_t>(storage.float32) ==
2802 base::bit_cast<uint32_t>(other.storage.float32);
2803 case Kind::kFloat64:
2804 case Kind::kNumber:
2805 // Using a bit_cast to uint64_t in order to return false when comparing
2806 // +0 and -0.
2807 // Note: for JavaScript, it would be fine to return true when both
2808 // values are NaNs, but for Wasm we must not merge NaNs that way.
2809 // Since we canonicalize NaNs for JS anyway, we don't need to treat
2810 // them specially here.
2811 return base::bit_cast<uint64_t>(storage.float64) ==
2812 base::bit_cast<uint64_t>(other.storage.float64);
2813 case Kind::kExternal:
2814 return storage.external.raw() == other.storage.external.raw();
2815 case Kind::kHeapObject:
2816 case Kind::kCompressedHeapObject:
2817 case Kind::kTrustedHeapObject:
2818 return storage.handle.address() == other.storage.handle.address();
2819 }
2820 }
2821};
2822
2823// Load `loaded_rep` from: base + offset + index * 2^element_size_log2.
2824// For Kind::tagged_base: subtract kHeapObjectTag,
2825// `base` has to be the object start.
2826// For (u)int8/16, the value will be sign- or zero-extended to Word32.
2827// When result_rep is RegisterRepresentation::Compressed(), then the load does
2828// not decompress the value.
2829struct LoadOp : OperationT<LoadOp> {
2830 struct Kind {
2831 // The `base` input is a tagged pointer to a HeapObject.
2832 bool tagged_base : 1;
2833 // The effective address might be unaligned. This is only set to true if
2834 // the platform does not support unaligned loads for the given
2835 // MemoryRepresentation natively.
2836 bool maybe_unaligned : 1;
2837 // There is a Wasm trap handler for out-of-bounds accesses.
2838 bool with_trap_handler : 1;
2839 // The wasm trap handler is used for null accesses. Note that this requires
2840 // with_trap_handler as well.
2841 bool trap_on_null : 1;
2842 // If {load_eliminable} is true, then:
2843 // - Stores/Loads at this address cannot overlap. Concretely, it means
2844 // that something like this cannot happen:
2845 //
2846 // const u32s = Uint32Array.of(3, 8);
2847 // const u8s = new Uint8Array(u32s.buffer);
2848 // u32s[0] = 0xffffffff;
2849 // u8s[1] = 0; // Overlaps with previous store!
2850 //
2851 // - Stores/Loads at this address have a canonical base. Concretely, it
2852 // means that something like this cannot happen:
2853 //
2854 // let buffer = new ArrayBuffer(10000);
2855 // let ta1 = new Int32Array(buffer, 0/*offset*/);
2856 // let ta2 = new Int32Array(buffer, 100*4/*offset*/);
2857 // ta2[0] = 0xff;
2858 // ta1[100] = 42; // Same destination as the previous store!
2859 //
2860 // - No other thread can modify the underlying value. E.g. in the case of
2861 // loading the wasm stack limit, other threads can modify the loaded
2862 // value, so we always have to reload it.
2863 //
2864 // This is mainly used for load elimination: when stores/loads don't have
2865 // the {load_eliminable} bit set to true, more things need to be
2866 // invalidated.
2867 // In the main JS pipeline, only ArrayBuffers (= TypedArray/DataView)
2868 // loads/stores have this {load_eliminable} set to false,
2869 // and all other loads have it to true.
2870 bool load_eliminable : 1;
2871 // The loaded value may not change.
2872 bool is_immutable : 1;
2873 // The load should be atomic.
2874 bool is_atomic : 1;
2875
2876 static constexpr Kind Aligned(BaseTaggedness base_is_tagged) {
2877 switch (base_is_tagged) {
2878 case BaseTaggedness::kTaggedBase:
2879 return TaggedBase();
2880 case BaseTaggedness::kUntaggedBase:
2881 return RawAligned();
2882 }
2883 }
2884 static constexpr Kind TaggedBase() {
2885 return {.tagged_base = true,
2886 .maybe_unaligned = false,
2887 .with_trap_handler = false,
2888 .trap_on_null = false,
2889 .load_eliminable = true,
2890 .is_immutable = false,
2891 .is_atomic = false};
2892 }
2893 static constexpr Kind RawAligned() {
2894 return {.tagged_base = false,
2895 .maybe_unaligned = false,
2896 .with_trap_handler = false,
2897 .trap_on_null = false,
2898 .load_eliminable = true,
2899 .is_immutable = false,
2900 .is_atomic = false};
2901 }
2902 static constexpr Kind RawUnaligned() {
2903 return {.tagged_base = false,
2904 .maybe_unaligned = true,
2905 .with_trap_handler = false,
2906 .trap_on_null = false,
2907 .load_eliminable = true,
2908 .is_immutable = false,
2909 .is_atomic = false};
2910 }
2911 static constexpr Kind Protected() {
2912 return {.tagged_base = false,
2913 .maybe_unaligned = false,
2914 .with_trap_handler = true,
2915 .trap_on_null = false,
2916 .load_eliminable = true,
2917 .is_immutable = false,
2918 .is_atomic = false};
2919 }
2920 static constexpr Kind TrapOnNull() {
2921 return {.tagged_base = true,
2922 .maybe_unaligned = false,
2923 .with_trap_handler = true,
2924 .trap_on_null = true,
2925 .load_eliminable = true,
2926 .is_immutable = false,
2927 .is_atomic = false};
2928 }
2929 static constexpr Kind MaybeUnaligned(MemoryRepresentation rep) {
2930 return rep == MemoryRepresentation::Int8() ||
2931 rep == MemoryRepresentation::Uint8() ||
2932 SupportedOperations::IsUnalignedLoadSupported(rep)
2933 ? LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned()
2934 : LoadOp::Kind::RawUnaligned();
2935 }
2936
2937 constexpr Kind NotLoadEliminable() {
2938 Kind new_kind = *this;
2939 new_kind.load_eliminable = false;
2940 return new_kind;
2941 }
2942
2943 constexpr Kind Immutable() const {
2944 Kind new_kind(*this);
2945 new_kind.is_immutable = true;
2946 return new_kind;
2947 }
2948
2949 constexpr Kind Atomic() const {
2950 Kind new_kind(*this);
2951 new_kind.is_atomic = true;
2952 return new_kind;
2953 }
2954
2955 bool operator==(const Kind& other) const {
2956 return tagged_base == other.tagged_base &&
2957 maybe_unaligned == other.maybe_unaligned &&
2958 with_trap_handler == other.with_trap_handler &&
2959 load_eliminable == other.load_eliminable &&
2960 is_immutable == other.is_immutable &&
2961 is_atomic == other.is_atomic && trap_on_null == other.trap_on_null;
2962 }
2963 };
2964 Kind kind;
2965 MemoryRepresentation loaded_rep;
2966 RegisterRepresentation result_rep;
2967 uint8_t element_size_log2; // multiply index with 2^element_size_log2
2968 int32_t offset; // add offset to scaled index
2969
2970 OpEffects Effects() const {
2971 // Loads might depend on checks for pointer validity, object layout, bounds
2972 // checks, etc.
2973 // TODO(tebbi): Distinguish between on-heap and off-heap loads.
2974 OpEffects effects = OpEffects().CanReadMemory().CanDependOnChecks();
2975 if (kind.with_trap_handler) effects = effects.CanLeaveCurrentFunction();
2976 if (kind.is_atomic) {
2977 // Atomic load should not be reordered with other loads.
2978 effects = effects.CanWriteMemory();
2979 }
2980 return effects;
2981 }
2982 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
2983 return base::VectorOf(&result_rep, 1);
2984 }
2985
2986 MachineType machine_type() const;
2987
2988 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
2989 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
2990 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> result =
2991 kind.tagged_base
2992 ? MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged(),
2993 MaybeRegisterRepresentation::WordPtr()>()
2994 : MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::WordPtr(),
2995 MaybeRegisterRepresentation::WordPtr()>();
2996 return index().valid() ? result : base::VectorOf(result.data(), 1);
2997 }
2998
2999 OpIndex base() const { return input(0); }
3000 OptionalOpIndex index() const {
3001 return input_count == 2 ? input(1) : OpIndex::Invalid();
3002 }
3003
3004 static constexpr bool OffsetIsValid(int32_t offset, bool tagged_base) {
3005 if (tagged_base) {
3006 // When a Load has the tagged_base Kind, it means that {offset} will
3007 // eventually need a "-kHeapObjectTag". If the {offset} is
3008 // min_int, then subtracting kHeapObjectTag will underflow.
3009 return offset >= std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min() + kHeapObjectTag;
3010 }
3011 return true;
3012 }
3013
3014 LoadOp(OpIndex base, OptionalOpIndex index, Kind kind,
3015 MemoryRepresentation loaded_rep, RegisterRepresentation result_rep,
3016 int32_t offset, uint8_t element_size_log2)
3017 : Base(1 + index.valid()),
3018 kind(kind),
3019 loaded_rep(loaded_rep),
3020 result_rep(result_rep),
3021 element_size_log2(element_size_log2),
3022 offset(offset) {
3023 input(0) = base;
3024 if (index.valid()) {
3025 input(1) = index.value();
3026 }
3027 }
3028
3029 template <typename Fn, typename Mapper>
3030 V8_INLINE auto Explode(Fn fn, Mapper& mapper) const {
3031 return fn(mapper.Map(base()), mapper.Map(index()), kind, loaded_rep,
3032 result_rep, offset, element_size_log2);
3033 }
3034
3035 void Validate(const Graph& graph) const {
3036 DCHECK(loaded_rep.ToRegisterRepresentation() == result_rep ||
3037 (loaded_rep.IsCompressibleTagged() &&
3038 result_rep == RegisterRepresentation::Compressed()) ||
3039 kind.is_atomic);
3040 DCHECK_IMPLIES(element_size_log2 > 0, index().valid());
3041 DCHECK_IMPLIES(kind.maybe_unaligned,
3042 !SupportedOperations::IsUnalignedLoadSupported(loaded_rep));
3043 DCHECK(OffsetIsValid(offset, kind.tagged_base));
3044 }
3045 static LoadOp& New(Graph* graph, OpIndex base, OptionalOpIndex index,
3046 Kind kind, MemoryRepresentation loaded_rep,
3047 RegisterRepresentation result_rep, int32_t offset,
3048 uint8_t element_size_log2) {
3049 return Base::New(graph, 1 + index.valid(), base, index, kind, loaded_rep,
3050 result_rep, offset, element_size_log2);
3051 }
3052 void PrintInputs(std::ostream& os, const std::string& op_index_prefix) const;
3053 void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;
3054 auto options() const {
3055 return std::tuple{kind, loaded_rep, result_rep, offset, element_size_log2};
3056 }
3057};
3058
3059V8_INLINE size_t hash_value(LoadOp::Kind kind) {
3060 return base::hash_value(
3061 static_cast<int>(kind.tagged_base) | (kind.maybe_unaligned << 1) |
3062 (kind.load_eliminable << 2) | (kind.is_immutable << 3) |
3063 (kind.with_trap_handler << 4) | (kind.is_atomic << 5));
3064}
3065
3066struct AtomicRMWOp : OperationT<AtomicRMWOp> {
3067 enum class BinOp : uint8_t {
3068 kAdd,
3069 kSub,
3070 kAnd,
3071 kOr,
3072 kXor,
3073 kExchange,
3074 kCompareExchange
3075 };
3076 BinOp bin_op;
3077 RegisterRepresentation in_out_rep;
3078 MemoryRepresentation memory_rep;
3079 MemoryAccessKind memory_access_kind;
3080 OpEffects Effects() const {
3081 OpEffects effects =
3082 OpEffects().CanWriteMemory().CanDependOnChecks().CanReadMemory();
3083 if (memory_access_kind == MemoryAccessKind::kProtectedByTrapHandler) {
3084 effects = effects.CanLeaveCurrentFunction();
3085 }
3086 return effects;
3087 }
3088
3089 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
3090 return base::VectorOf(&in_out_rep, 1);
3091 }
3092
3093 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
3094 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
3095 if (bin_op == BinOp::kCompareExchange) {
3096 return InitVectorOf(
3097 storage, {RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr(),
3098 RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr(), in_out_rep, in_out_rep});
3099 }
3100 return InitVectorOf(storage,
3101 {RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr(),
3102 RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr(), in_out_rep});
3103 }
3104
3105 V<WordPtr> base() const { return input<WordPtr>(0); }
3106 V<WordPtr> index() const { return input<WordPtr>(1); }
3107 OpIndex value() const { return input(2); }
3108 OptionalOpIndex expected() const {
3109 return (input_count == 4) ? input(3) : OpIndex::Invalid();
3110 }
3111
3112 void Validate(const Graph& graph) const {
3113 DCHECK_EQ(bin_op == BinOp::kCompareExchange, expected().valid());
3114 }
3115
3116 AtomicRMWOp(OpIndex base, OpIndex index, OpIndex value,
3117 OptionalOpIndex expected, BinOp bin_op,
3118 RegisterRepresentation in_out_rep,
3119 MemoryRepresentation memory_rep, MemoryAccessKind kind)
3120 : Base(3 + expected.valid()),
3121 bin_op(bin_op),
3122 in_out_rep(in_out_rep),
3123 memory_rep(memory_rep),
3124 memory_access_kind(kind) {
3125 input(0) = base;
3126 input(1) = index;
3127 input(2) = value;
3128 if (expected.valid()) {
3129 input(3) = expected.value();
3130 }
3131 }
3132
3133 template <typename Fn, typename Mapper>
3134 V8_INLINE auto Explode(Fn fn, Mapper& mapper) const {
3135 return fn(mapper.Map(base()), mapper.Map(index()), mapper.Map(value()),
3136 mapper.Map(expected()), bin_op, in_out_rep, memory_rep,
3137 memory_access_kind);
3138 }
3139
3140 static AtomicRMWOp& New(Graph* graph, OpIndex base, OpIndex index,
3141 OpIndex value, OptionalOpIndex expected, BinOp bin_op,
3142 RegisterRepresentation result_rep,
3143 MemoryRepresentation input_rep,
3144 MemoryAccessKind kind) {
3145 return Base::New(graph, 3 + expected.valid(), base, index, value, expected,
3146 bin_op, result_rep, input_rep, kind);
3147 }
3148
3149 void PrintInputs(std::ostream& os, const std::string& op_index_prefix) const;
3150
3151 void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;
3152
3153 auto options() const {
3154 return std::tuple{bin_op, in_out_rep, memory_rep, memory_access_kind};
3155 }
3156};
3157DEFINE_MULTI_SWITCH_INTEGRAL(AtomicRMWOp::BinOp, 8)
3158
3159V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os,
3160 AtomicRMWOp::BinOp kind);
3161
3162struct AtomicWord32PairOp : OperationT<AtomicWord32PairOp> {
3163 enum class Kind : uint8_t {
3164 kAdd,
3165 kSub,
3166 kAnd,
3167 kOr,
3168 kXor,
3169 kExchange,
3170 kCompareExchange,
3171 kLoad,
3172 kStore
3173 };
3174
3175 Kind kind;
3176 int32_t offset;
3177
3178 static Kind KindFromBinOp(AtomicRMWOp::BinOp bin_op) {
3179 switch (bin_op) {
3180 case AtomicRMWOp::BinOp::kAdd:
3181 return Kind::kAdd;
3182 case AtomicRMWOp::BinOp::kSub:
3183 return Kind::kSub;
3184 case AtomicRMWOp::BinOp::kAnd:
3185 return Kind::kAnd;
3186 case AtomicRMWOp::BinOp::kOr:
3187 return Kind::kOr;
3188 case AtomicRMWOp::BinOp::kXor:
3189 return Kind::kXor;
3190 case AtomicRMWOp::BinOp::kExchange:
3191 return Kind::kExchange;
3192 case AtomicRMWOp::BinOp::kCompareExchange:
3193 return Kind::kCompareExchange;
3194 }
3195 }
3196
3197 OpEffects Effects() const {
3198 OpEffects effects = OpEffects().CanDependOnChecks();
3199 if (kind == Kind::kStore) {
3200 return effects.CanWriteMemory();
3201 }
3202 // Atomic loads are marked as "can write memory" as they should not be
3203 // reordered with other loads. Secondly, they may not be removed even if
3204 // unused as they might make writes of other threads visible.
3205 return effects.CanReadMemory().CanWriteMemory();
3206 }
3207
3208 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
3209 if (kind == Kind::kStore) return {};
3210 return RepVector<RegisterRepresentation::Word32(),
3211 RegisterRepresentation::Word32()>();
3212 }
3213 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
3214 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
3215 storage.resize(input_count);
3216
3217 const bool has_index = HasIndex();
3218 storage[0] = RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr(); // base
3219 if (has_index) {
3220 storage[1] = RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr(); // index
3221 }
3222 if (kind != Kind::kLoad) {
3223 storage[1 + has_index] = RegisterRepresentation::Word32(); // value_low
3224 storage[2 + has_index] = RegisterRepresentation::Word32(); // value_high
3225 if (kind == Kind::kCompareExchange) {
3226 storage[3 + has_index] =
3227 RegisterRepresentation::Word32(); // expected_low
3228 storage[4 + has_index] =
3229 RegisterRepresentation::Word32(); // expected_high
3230 }
3231 }
3232 return base::VectorOf(storage);
3233 }
3234
3235 V<WordPtr> base() const { return input<WordPtr>(0); }
3236 OptionalV<WordPtr> index() const {
3237 return HasIndex() ? input<WordPtr>(1) : V<WordPtr>::Invalid();
3238 }
3239 OptionalV<Word32> value_low() const {
3240 return kind != Kind::kLoad ? input<Word32>(1 + HasIndex())
3241 : V<Word32>::Invalid();
3242 }
3243 OptionalV<Word32> value_high() const {
3244 return kind != Kind::kLoad ? input<Word32>(2 + HasIndex())
3245 : V<Word32>::Invalid();
3246 }
3247 OptionalV<Word32> expected_low() const {
3248 return kind == Kind::kCompareExchange ? input<Word32>(3 + HasIndex())
3249 : V<Word32>::Invalid();
3250 }
3251 OptionalV<Word32> expected_high() const {
3252 return kind == Kind::kCompareExchange ? input<Word32>(4 + HasIndex())
3253 : V<Word32>::Invalid();
3254 }
3255
3256
3257 AtomicWord32PairOp(V<WordPtr> base, OptionalV<WordPtr> index,
3258 OptionalV<Word32> value_low, OptionalV<Word32> value_high,
3259 OptionalV<Word32> expected_low,
3260 OptionalV<Word32> expected_high, Kind kind, int32_t offset)
3261 : Base(InputCount(kind, index.has_value())), kind(kind), offset(offset) {
3262 DCHECK_EQ(value_low.valid(), value_high.valid());
3263 DCHECK_EQ(expected_low.valid(), expected_high.valid());
3264 DCHECK_EQ(kind == Kind::kCompareExchange, expected_low.valid());
3265 DCHECK_EQ(kind != Kind::kLoad, value_low.valid());
3266
3267 const bool has_index = index.has_value();
3268 DCHECK_EQ(has_index, HasIndex());
3269
3270 input(0) = base;
3271 if (has_index) input(1) = index.value();
3272 if (kind != Kind::kLoad) {
3273 input(1 + has_index) = value_low.value();
3274 input(2 + has_index) = value_high.value();
3275 if (kind == Kind::kCompareExchange) {
3276 input(3 + has_index) = expected_low.value();
3277 input(4 + has_index) = expected_high.value();
3278 }
3279 }
3280 }
3281
3282 template <typename Fn, typename Mapper>
3283 V8_INLINE auto Explode(Fn fn, Mapper& mapper) const {
3284 return fn(mapper.Map(base()), mapper.Map(index()), mapper.Map(value_low()),
3285 mapper.Map(value_high()), mapper.Map(expected_low()),
3286 mapper.Map(expected_high()), kind, offset);
3287 }
3288
3289 static constexpr size_t InputCount(Kind kind, bool has_index) {
3290 switch (kind) {
3291 case Kind::kLoad:
3292 return 1 + has_index; // base, index?
3293 case Kind::kAdd:
3294 case Kind::kSub:
3295 case Kind::kAnd:
3296 case Kind::kOr:
3297 case Kind::kXor:
3298 case Kind::kExchange:
3299 case Kind::kStore:
3300 return 3 + has_index; // base, index?, value_low, value_high
3301 case Kind::kCompareExchange:
3302 return 5 + has_index; // base, index?, value_low, value_high,
3303 // expected_low, expected_high
3304 }
3305 }
3306 bool HasIndex() const { return input_count == InputCount(kind, true); }
3307
3308 static AtomicWord32PairOp& New(Graph* graph, V<WordPtr> base,
3309 OptionalV<WordPtr> index,
3310 OptionalV<Word32> value_low,
3311 OptionalV<Word32> value_high,
3312 OptionalV<Word32> expected_low,
3313 OptionalV<Word32> expected_high, Kind kind,
3314 int32_t offset) {
3315 return Base::New(graph, InputCount(kind, index.has_value()), base, index,
3316 value_low, value_high, expected_low, expected_high, kind,
3317 offset);
3318 }
3319
3320 void PrintInputs(std::ostream& os, const std::string& op_index_prefix) const;
3321
3322 void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;
3323
3324 auto options() const { return std::tuple{kind, offset}; }
3325};
3326
3327V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os,
3328 AtomicWord32PairOp::Kind kind);

3339 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const { return {}; }

3342 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {

3350
3351// Store `value` to: base + offset + index * 2^element_size_log2.
3352// For Kind::tagged_base: subtract kHeapObjectTag,
3353// `base` has to be the object start.
3354struct StoreOp : OperationT<StoreOp> {
3355 using Kind = LoadOp::Kind;
3356 Kind kind;
3357 MemoryRepresentation stored_rep;
3358 WriteBarrierKind write_barrier;
3359 uint8_t element_size_log2; // multiply index with 2^element_size_log2
3360 int32_t offset; // add offset to scaled index
3361 bool maybe_initializing_or_transitioning;
3362 uint16_t
3363 shifted_indirect_pointer_tag; // for indirect pointer stores, the
3364 // IndirectPointerTag of the store shifted
3365 // to the right by kIndirectPointerTagShift
3366 // (so it fits into 16 bits).
3367 // TODO(saelo): now that we have a pointer tag in these low-level operations,
3368 // we could also consider passing the external pointer tag (for external
3369 // pointers) through to the macro assembler (where we have routines to work
3370 // with external pointers) instead of handling those earlier in the compiler.
3371 // We might lose the ability to hardcode the table address though.
3372
3373 OpEffects Effects() const {
3374 // Stores might depend on checks for pointer validity, object layout, bounds
3375 // checks, etc.
3376 // TODO(tebbi): Distinghish between on-heap and off-heap stores.
3377 OpEffects effects = OpEffects().CanWriteMemory().CanDependOnChecks();
3378 if (kind.with_trap_handler) effects = effects.CanLeaveCurrentFunction();
3379 if (maybe_initializing_or_transitioning) {
3380 effects = effects.CanDoRawHeapAccess();
3381 }
3382 if (kind.is_atomic) {
3383 // Atomic stores should not be eliminated away, even if the situation
3384 // seems to allow e.g. store-store elimination. Elimination is avoided by
3385 // setting the `CanReadMemory` effect.
3386 effects = effects.CanReadMemory();
3387 }
3388 return effects;
3389 }
3390 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const { return {}; }
3391
3392 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
3393 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
3394 RegisterRepresentation base = kind.tagged_base
3395 ? RegisterRepresentation::Tagged()
3396 : RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr();
3397 if (index() == OpIndex::Invalid()) {
3398 return InitVectorOf(
3399 storage, {base, stored_rep.ToRegisterRepresentationForStore()});
3400 }
3401 return InitVectorOf(storage,
3402 {base, stored_rep.ToRegisterRepresentationForStore(),
3403 RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr()});
3404 }
3405
3406 OpIndex base() const { return input(0); }
3407 OpIndex value() const { return input(1); }
3408 OptionalOpIndex index() const {
3409 return input_count == 3 ? input(2) : OpIndex::Invalid();
3410 }
3411
3412 IndirectPointerTag indirect_pointer_tag() const {
3413 uint64_t shifted = shifted_indirect_pointer_tag;
3414 return static_cast<IndirectPointerTag>(shifted << kIndirectPointerTagShift);
3415 }
3416
3417 StoreOp(
3418 OpIndex base, OptionalOpIndex index, OpIndex value, Kind kind,
3419 MemoryRepresentation stored_rep, WriteBarrierKind write_barrier,
3420 int32_t offset, uint8_t element_size_log2,
3421 bool maybe_initializing_or_transitioning,
3422 IndirectPointerTag maybe_indirect_pointer_tag = kIndirectPointerNullTag)
3423 : Base(2 + index.valid()),
3424 kind(kind),
3425 stored_rep(stored_rep),
3426 write_barrier(write_barrier),
3427 element_size_log2(element_size_log2),
3428 offset(offset),
3429 maybe_initializing_or_transitioning(
3430 maybe_initializing_or_transitioning),
3431 shifted_indirect_pointer_tag(maybe_indirect_pointer_tag >>
3432 kIndirectPointerTagShift) {
3433 DCHECK_EQ(indirect_pointer_tag(), maybe_indirect_pointer_tag);
3434 input(0) = base;
3435 input(1) = value;
3436 if (index.valid()) {
3437 input(2) = index.value();
3438 }
3439 }
3440
3441 template <typename Fn, typename Mapper>
3442 V8_INLINE auto Explode(Fn fn, Mapper& mapper) const {
3443 return fn(mapper.Map(base()), mapper.Map(index()), mapper.Map(value()),
3444 kind, stored_rep, write_barrier, offset, element_size_log2,
3445 maybe_initializing_or_transitioning, indirect_pointer_tag());
3446 }
3447
3448 void Validate(const Graph& graph) const {
3449 DCHECK_IMPLIES(element_size_log2 > 0, index().valid());
3450 DCHECK_IMPLIES(kind.maybe_unaligned,
3451 !SupportedOperations::IsUnalignedLoadSupported(stored_rep));
3452 DCHECK(LoadOp::OffsetIsValid(offset, kind.tagged_base));
3453 }
3454 static StoreOp& New(
3455 Graph* graph, OpIndex base, OptionalOpIndex index, OpIndex value,
3456 Kind kind, MemoryRepresentation stored_rep,
3457 WriteBarrierKind write_barrier, int32_t offset, uint8_t element_size_log2,
3458 bool maybe_initializing_or_transitioning,
3459 IndirectPointerTag maybe_indirect_pointer_tag = kIndirectPointerNullTag) {
3460 return Base::New(graph, 2 + index.valid(), base, index, value, kind,
3461 stored_rep, write_barrier, offset, element_size_log2,
3462 maybe_initializing_or_transitioning,
3463 maybe_indirect_pointer_tag);
3464 }
3465
3466 void PrintInputs(std::ostream& os, const std::string& op_index_prefix) const;
3467 void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;
3468 auto options() const {
3469 return std::tuple{
3470 kind, stored_rep, write_barrier,
3471 offset, element_size_log2, maybe_initializing_or_transitioning};
3472 }
3473};

3475struct AllocateOp : FixedArityOperationT<1, AllocateOp> {

3479 OpEffects()
3480 .CanAllocate()
3481 // The resulting object is unitialized, which leaves the heap in an
3482 // inconsistent state.
3483 .CanDoRawHeapAccess()
3484 // Do not move allocations before checks, to avoid OOM or invalid
3485 // size.

3497
3498 AllocateOp(V<WordPtr> size, AllocationType type) : Base(size), type(type) {}
3499
3500 void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;
3501
3502 auto options() const { return std::tuple{type}; }
3503};

3505struct DecodeExternalPointerOp
3506 : FixedArityOperationT<1, DecodeExternalPointerOp> {
3507 ExternalPointerTagRange tag_range;
3508
3509 // Accessing external pointers is only safe if the garbage collected pointer
3510 // keeping the external pointer alive is retained for the length of the
3511 // operation. For this, it is essential that we use a `Retain` operation
3512 // placed after the last access to the external data.
3513 static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects();

3515 return RepVector<RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr()>();
3516 }
3517
3518 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(

3520 return MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Word32()>();
3521 }

3526 : Base(handle), tag_range(tag_range) {}

3528 void Validate(const Graph& graph) const { DCHECK(!tag_range.IsEmpty()); }
3529 void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;

3533struct JSStackCheckOp : OperationT<JSStackCheckOp> {
3534 enum class Kind : uint8_t { kFunctionEntry, kBuiltinEntry, kLoop };
3535 Kind kind;
3536
3537 OpEffects Effects() const {
3538 switch (kind) {
3539 case Kind::kFunctionEntry:
3540 return OpEffects().CanCallAnything();
3541 case Kind::kBuiltinEntry:
3542 return OpEffects().CanCallAnything();
3543 case Kind::kLoop:
3544 // Loop body iteration stack checks can't write memory.
3545 // TODO(dmercadier): we could prevent this from allocating. In
3546 // particular, we'd need to:
3547 // - forbid GC interrupts from being processed in loop stack checks.
3548 // - make sure that the debugger always deopts the current function
3549 // when it triggers a loop interrupt.
3550 return OpEffects()
3551 .CanDependOnChecks()
3552 .CanDeopt()
3553 .CanReadHeapMemory()
3554 .CanAllocate();
3555 }
3556 }
3557
3558 V<Context> native_context() const { return Base::input<Context>(0); }
3559 OptionalV<FrameState> frame_state() const {
3560 return input_count > 1 ? Base::input<FrameState>(1)
3561 : OptionalV<FrameState>::Nullopt();
3562 }
3563
3564 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const { return {}; }
3565
3566 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
3567 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
3568 return {};
3569 }
3570
3571 explicit JSStackCheckOp(V<Context> context, OptionalV<FrameState> frame_state,
3572 Kind kind)
3573 : Base(1 + frame_state.has_value()), kind(kind) {
3574 input(0) = context;
3575 if (frame_state.has_value()) {
3576 input(1) = frame_state.value();
3577 }
3578 }
3579
3580 static JSStackCheckOp& New(Graph* graph, V<Context> context,
3581 OptionalV<FrameState> frame_state, Kind kind) {
3582 return Base::New(graph, 1 + frame_state.has_value(), context, frame_state,
3583 kind);
3584 }
3585
3586 void Validate(const Graph& graph) const {
3587 DCHECK_EQ(kind == Kind::kBuiltinEntry, !frame_state().has_value());
3588 }
3589
3590 template <typename Fn, typename Mapper>
3591 V8_INLINE auto Explode(Fn fn, Mapper& mapper) const {
3592 return fn(mapper.Map(native_context()), mapper.Map(frame_state()), kind);
3593 }
3594
3595 auto options() const { return std::tuple{kind}; }
3596};

3598// Retain a HeapObject to prevent it from being garbage collected too early.
3599struct RetainOp : FixedArityOperationT<1, RetainOp> {
3600 V<Object> retained() const { return input<Object>(0); }
3601
3602 // Retain doesn't actually write, it just keeps a value alive. However, since
3603 // this must not be reordered with reading operations, we mark it as writing.
3604 static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects().CanWriteMemory();
3605 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const { return {}; }
3606
3607 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
3608 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
3609 return MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged()>();
3610 }
3611
3612 explicit RetainOp(V<Object> retained) : Base(retained) {}
3613
3614 auto options() const { return std::tuple{}; }
3615};

3701struct FrameStateOp : OperationT<FrameStateOp> {
3702 bool inlined;
3703 const FrameStateData* data;
3704
3705 static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects();
3706 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const { return {}; }
3707
3708 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
3709 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
3710 return {};
3711 }
3712
3713 OpIndex parent_frame_state() const {
3714 DCHECK(inlined);
3715 return input(0);
3716 }
3717 base::Vector<const OpIndex> state_values() const {
3718 base::Vector<const OpIndex> result = inputs();
3719 if (inlined) result += 1;
3720 return result;
3721 }
3722 uint16_t state_values_count() const {
3723 DCHECK_EQ(input_count - inlined, state_values().size());
3724 return input_count - inlined;
3725 }
3726 const OpIndex state_value(size_t idx) const { return state_values()[idx]; }
3727
3728 RegisterRepresentation state_value_rep(size_t idx) const {
3729 return RegisterRepresentation::FromMachineRepresentation(
3730 data->machine_types[idx].representation());
3731 }

3734 const FrameStateData* data)
3735 : Base(inputs), inlined(inlined), data(data) {}

3738 V8_INLINE auto Explode(Fn fn, Mapper& mapper) const {
3739 auto mapped_inputs = mapper.template Map<32>(inputs());
3740 return fn(base::VectorOf(mapped_inputs), inlined, data);
3741 }
3742
3743 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE void Validate(const Graph& graph) const;
3744 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;

3770struct DeoptimizeIfOp : FixedArityOperationT<2, DeoptimizeIfOp> {
3771 bool negated;
3772 const DeoptimizeParameters* parameters;
3773
3774 static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects().CanDeopt();
3775 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const { return {}; }
3776
3777 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
3778 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
3779 return MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Word32()>();
3780 }
3781
3782 V<Word32> condition() const { return input<Word32>(0); }
3783 V<FrameState> frame_state() const { return input<FrameState>(1); }
3784
3785 DeoptimizeIfOp(V<Word32> condition, V<FrameState> frame_state, bool negated,
3786 const DeoptimizeParameters* parameters)
3787 : Base(condition, frame_state),
3788 negated(negated),
3789 parameters(parameters) {}
3790
3791 bool EqualsForGVN(const DeoptimizeIfOp& other) const {
3792 // As far as GVN is concerned, the `frame_state` and `parameters` don't
3793 // matter: 2 DeoptimizeIf can be GVNed if they have the same `condition` and
3794 // same `negated`, regardless of their `frame_state` and `parameters`.
3795 return condition() == other.condition() && negated == other.negated;
3796 }
3797 size_t hash_value(
3798 HashingStrategy strategy = HashingStrategy::kDefault) const {
3799 // To enable GVNing as described above in `EqualsForGVN`, `hash_value` has
3800 // to ignore the `frame_state` and the `parameters`.
3801 return fast_hash_combine(Opcode::kDeoptimizeIf, condition(), negated);
3802 }
3803 void Validate(const Graph& graph) const {
3804 DCHECK(Get(graph, frame_state()).Is<FrameStateOp>());
3805 }
3806 auto options() const { return std::tuple{negated, parameters}; }
3807 void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;
3808};

3812struct WasmStackCheckOp : FixedArityOperationT<0, WasmStackCheckOp> {

3814 Kind kind;
3815
3816 static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects().CanCallAnything();

3820 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const { return {}; }
3821
3822 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
3823 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
3824 return {};
3825 }
3826
3827
3828 auto options() const { return std::tuple{kind}; }
3829};

3831V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os,
3832 WasmStackCheckOp::Kind kind);
3833struct TrapIfOp : OperationT<TrapIfOp> {
3834 bool negated;
3835 const TrapId trap_id;
3836
3837 static constexpr OpEffects effects =
3838 OpEffects()
3839 // Traps must not float above a protective check.
3840 .CanDependOnChecks()
3841 // Subsequent code can rely on the trap not having happened.
3842 .CanLeaveCurrentFunction();
3843 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const { return {}; }
3844
3845 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
3846 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
3847 return MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Word32()>();
3848 }
3849
3850 V<Word32> condition() const { return input<Word32>(0); }
3851 OptionalV<FrameState> frame_state() const {
3852 return input_count > 1 ? input<FrameState>(1)
3853 : OptionalV<FrameState>::Nullopt();
3854 }
3855
3856 TrapIfOp(V<Word32> condition, OptionalV<FrameState> frame_state, bool negated,
3857 const TrapId trap_id)
3858 : Base(1 + frame_state.valid()), negated(negated), trap_id(trap_id) {
3859 input(0) = condition;
3860 if (frame_state.valid()) {
3861 input(1) = frame_state.value();
3862 }
3863 }
3864
3865 template <typename Fn, typename Mapper>
3866 V8_INLINE auto Explode(Fn fn, Mapper& mapper) const {
3867 return fn(mapper.Map(condition()), mapper.Map(frame_state()), negated,
3868 trap_id);
3869 }
3870
3871 static TrapIfOp& New(Graph* graph, V<Word32> condition,
3872 OptionalV<FrameState> frame_state, bool negated,
3873 const TrapId trap_id) {
3874 return Base::New(graph, 1 + frame_state.valid(), condition, frame_state,
3875 negated, trap_id);
3876 }
3877
3878 void Validate(const Graph& graph) const {
3879 if (frame_state().valid()) {
3880 DCHECK(Get(graph, frame_state().value()).Is<FrameStateOp>());
3881 }
3882 }
3883 auto options() const { return std::tuple{negated, trap_id}; }
3884};
3885#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY

3949struct TSCallDescriptor : public NON_EXPORTED_BASE(ZoneObject) {
3950 const CallDescriptor* descriptor;
3951 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> in_reps;
3952 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> out_reps;
3953 CanThrow can_throw;
3954 LazyDeoptOnThrow lazy_deopt_on_throw;
3955 // TODO(dlehmann,353475584): Since the `JSWasmCallParameters` are specific to
3956 // one particular call site, this assumes that (only works correctly if)
3957 // `TSCallDescriptor`s are not shared across different calls (which they are
3958 // not at the moment).
3959 // For sharing call descriptors, the `JSWasmCallParameters` need to be moved
3960 // to the CallOp, which causes a lot of code churn (needs touching all
3961 // `REDUCE(Call)`).
3962 const JSWasmCallParameters* js_wasm_call_parameters;
3963
3964 TSCallDescriptor(const CallDescriptor* descriptor,
3965 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> in_reps,
3966 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> out_reps,
3967 CanThrow can_throw, LazyDeoptOnThrow lazy_deopt_on_throw,
3968 const JSWasmCallParameters* js_wasm_call_parameters)
3969 : descriptor(descriptor),
3970 in_reps(in_reps),
3971 out_reps(out_reps),
3972 can_throw(can_throw),
3973 lazy_deopt_on_throw(lazy_deopt_on_throw),
3974 js_wasm_call_parameters(js_wasm_call_parameters) {}
3975
3976 static const TSCallDescriptor* Create(
3977 const CallDescriptor* descriptor, CanThrow can_throw,
3978 LazyDeoptOnThrow lazy_deopt_on_throw, Zone* graph_zone,
3979 const JSWasmCallParameters* js_wasm_call_parameters = nullptr) {
3980 DCHECK_IMPLIES(can_throw == CanThrow::kNo,
3981 lazy_deopt_on_throw == LazyDeoptOnThrow::kNo);
3982 base::Vector<RegisterRepresentation> in_reps =
3983 graph_zone->AllocateVector<RegisterRepresentation>(
3984 descriptor->ParameterCount());
3985 for (size_t i = 0; i < descriptor->ParameterCount(); ++i) {
3986 in_reps[i] = RegisterRepresentation::FromMachineRepresentation(
3987 descriptor->GetParameterType(i).representation());
3988 }
3989 base::Vector<RegisterRepresentation> out_reps =
3990 graph_zone->AllocateVector<RegisterRepresentation>(
3991 descriptor->ReturnCount());
3992 for (size_t i = 0; i < descriptor->ReturnCount(); ++i) {
3993 out_reps[i] = RegisterRepresentation::FromMachineRepresentation(
3994 descriptor->GetReturnType(i).representation());
3995 }
3996 return graph_zone->New<TSCallDescriptor>(descriptor, in_reps, out_reps,
3997 can_throw, lazy_deopt_on_throw,
3998 js_wasm_call_parameters);
3999 }
4000};
4001
4002template <>
4003struct fast_hash<TSCallDescriptor> {
4004 size_t operator()(const TSCallDescriptor& v) {
4005 const CallDescriptor& d = *v.descriptor;
4006 // This does not include all fields of the call descriptor, but it should be
4007 // sufficient to differentiate between different calls (and collisions are
4008 // not too critical).
4009 return fast_hash_combine(d.kind(), d.tag(), d.ReturnCount(),
4010 d.ParameterCount(), d.GPParameterCount(),
4011 d.FPParameterCount(), d.ParameterSlotCount(),
4012 d.ReturnSlotCount(), d.flags());
4013 }
4014};

4016// If {target} is a HeapObject representing a builtin, return that builtin's ID.
4017std::optional<Builtin> TryGetBuiltinId(const ConstantOp* target,
4018 JSHeapBroker* broker);

4020struct CallOp : OperationT<CallOp> {
4021 const TSCallDescriptor* descriptor;
4022 OpEffects callee_effects;
4023
4024 OpEffects Effects() const { return callee_effects; }
4025
4026 // The outputs are produced by the `DidntThrow` operation.
4027 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const { return {}; }
4028 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> results_rep() const {
4029 return descriptor->out_reps;
4030 }
4031
4032 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
4033 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
4034 storage.resize(input_count);
4035 size_t i = 0;
4036 if (descriptor->descriptor->IsCodeObjectCall() ||
4037 descriptor->descriptor->IsJSFunctionCall() ||
4038 descriptor->descriptor->IsBuiltinPointerCall()) {
4039 storage[i++] = MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged();
4040#ifdef V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4041 } else if (descriptor->descriptor->IsIndirectWasmFunctionCall()) {
4042 storage[i++] = MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Word32();
4043#endif
4044 } else {
4045 storage[i++] = MaybeRegisterRepresentation::WordPtr();
4046 }
4047 if (HasFrameState()) {
4048 storage[i++] = MaybeRegisterRepresentation::None();
4049 }
4050 for (auto rep : descriptor->in_reps) {
4051 // In JavaScript, parameters are optional.
4052 if (i >= input_count) break;
4053 storage[i++] = rep;
4054 }
4055 storage.resize(i);
4056 return base::VectorOf(storage);
4057 }
4058
4059 bool HasFrameState() const {
4060 return descriptor->descriptor->NeedsFrameState();
4061 }
4062
4063 V<CallTarget> callee() const { return input<CallTarget>(0); }
4064 OptionalV<FrameState> frame_state() const {
4065 return HasFrameState() ? input<FrameState>(1)
4066 : OptionalV<FrameState>::Nullopt();
4067 }
4068 base::Vector<const OpIndex> arguments() const {
4069 return inputs().SubVector(1 + HasFrameState(), input_count);
4070 }
4071 // Returns true if this call is a JS (but not wasm) stack check.
4072 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE bool IsStackCheck(const Graph& graph, JSHeapBroker* broker,
4073 StackCheckKind kind) const;
4074
4075 CallOp(V<CallTarget> callee, OptionalV<FrameState> frame_state,
4076 base::Vector<const OpIndex> arguments,
4077 const TSCallDescriptor* descriptor, OpEffects effects)
4078 : Base(1 + frame_state.valid() + arguments.size()),
4079 descriptor(descriptor),
4080 callee_effects(effects) {
4081 base::Vector<OpIndex> inputs = this->inputs();
4082 inputs[0] = callee;
4083 if (frame_state.valid()) {
4084 inputs[1] = frame_state.value();
4085 }
4086 inputs.SubVector(1 + frame_state.valid(), inputs.size())
4087 .OverwriteWith(arguments);
4088 }
4089
4090 template <typename Fn, typename Mapper>
4091 V8_INLINE auto Explode(Fn fn, Mapper& mapper) const {
4092 V<CallTarget> mapped_callee = mapper.Map(callee());
4093 OptionalV<FrameState> mapped_frame_state = mapper.Map(frame_state());
4094 auto mapped_arguments = mapper.template Map<16>(arguments());
4095 return fn(mapped_callee, mapped_frame_state,
4096 base::VectorOf(mapped_arguments), descriptor, Effects());
4097 }
4098
4099 void Validate(const Graph& graph) const {
4100 if (frame_state().valid()) {
4101 DCHECK(Get(graph, frame_state().value()).Is<FrameStateOp>());
4102 }
4103 }
4104
4105 static CallOp& New(Graph* graph, V<CallTarget> callee,
4106 OptionalV<FrameState> frame_state,
4107 base::Vector<const OpIndex> arguments,
4108 const TSCallDescriptor* descriptor, OpEffects effects) {
4109 return Base::New(graph, 1 + frame_state.valid() + arguments.size(), callee,
4110 frame_state, arguments, descriptor, effects);
4111 }
4112 // TODO(mliedtke): Should the hash function be overwritten, so that calls (and
4113 // potentially tail calls) can participate in GVN? Right now this is prevented
4114 // by every call descriptor being a different pointer.
4115 auto options() const { return std::tuple{descriptor, callee_effects}; }
4116 size_t hash_value(HashingStrategy strategy = HashingStrategy::kDefault) const;
4117 void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;
4118};

4120// Catch an exception from the first operation of the `successor` block and
4121// continue execution in `catch_block` in this case.
4122struct CheckExceptionOp : FixedArityOperationT<1, CheckExceptionOp> {
4123 Block* didnt_throw_block;
4124 Block* catch_block;
4125
4126 static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects().CanCallAnything();
4127 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const { return {}; }
4128
4129 V<Any> throwing_operation() const { return input<Any>(0); }
4130
4131 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
4132 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
4133 return {};
4134 }
4135
4136 CheckExceptionOp(V<Any> throwing_operation, Block* successor,
4137 Block* catch_block)
4138 : Base(throwing_operation),
4139 didnt_throw_block(successor),
4140 catch_block(catch_block) {}
4141
4142 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE void Validate(const Graph& graph) const;
4143
4144 size_t hash_value(HashingStrategy strategy = HashingStrategy::kDefault) const;
4145 auto options() const { return std::tuple{didnt_throw_block, catch_block}; }
4146};

4148// This is a pseudo-operation that marks the beginning of a catch block. It
4149// returns the caught exception.
4150struct CatchBlockBeginOp : FixedArityOperationT<0, CatchBlockBeginOp> {
4151 static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects().CanCallAnything();
4152
4153 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
4154 return RepVector<RegisterRepresentation::Tagged()>();
4155 }
4156
4157 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
4158 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
4159 return {};
4160 }
4161
4162 CatchBlockBeginOp() : Base() {}
4163 auto options() const { return std::tuple{}; }
4164};
4165
4166// Throwing operations always appear together with `DidntThrowOp`, which
4167// produces the value in case that no exception was thrown. If the callsite is
4168// non-catching, then `DidntThrowOp` follows right after the throwing operation:
4169//
4170// 100: Call(...)
4171// 101: DidntThrow(100)
4172// 102: Foo(101)
4173//
4174// If the callsite can catch, then the
4175// pattern is as follows:
4176//
4177// 100: Call(...)
4178// 101: CheckException(B10, B11)
4179//
4180// B10:
4181// 102: DidntThrow(100)
4182// 103: Foo(102)
4183//
4184// B11:
4185// 200: CatchBlockBegin()
4186// 201: ...
4187//
4188// This complexity is mostly hidden from graph creation, with
4189// `DidntThrowOp` and `CheckExceptionOp` being inserted automatically.
4190// The correct way to produce `CheckExceptionOp` is to create an
4191// `Assembler::CatchScope`, which will cause all throwing operations
4192// to add a `CheckExceptionOp` automatically while the scope is active.
4193// Since `CopyingPhase` does this automatically, lowering throwing
4194// operations into an arbitrary subgraph works automatically.
4195struct DidntThrowOp : FixedArityOperationT<1, DidntThrowOp> {
4196 OpEffects throwing_op_effects;
4197
4198 // If there is a `CheckException` operation with a catch block for
4199 // `throwing_operation`.
4200 bool has_catch_block;
4201 // This is a pointer to a vector instead of a vector to save a bit of memory,
4202 // using optimal 16 bytes instead of 24.
4203 const base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation>* results_rep;
4204
4205 OpEffects Effects() const { return throwing_op_effects; }
4206
4207 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
4208 return *results_rep;
4209 }
4210
4211 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
4212 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
4213 return MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::None()>();
4214 }
4215
4216 OpIndex throwing_operation() const { return input(0); }
4217
4218 explicit DidntThrowOp(
4219 OpIndex throwing_operation, bool has_catch_block,
4220 const base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation>* results_rep,
4221 OpEffects throwing_op_effects)
4222 : Base(throwing_operation),
4223 throwing_op_effects(throwing_op_effects),
4224 has_catch_block(has_catch_block),
4225 results_rep(results_rep) {}
4226 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE void Validate(const Graph& graph) const;
4227 auto options() const {
4228 return std::tuple{throwing_op_effects, has_catch_block};
4229 }
4230};
4231
4232struct TailCallOp : OperationT<TailCallOp> {
4233 const TSCallDescriptor* descriptor;
4234
4235 static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects().CanLeaveCurrentFunction();
4236 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
4237 // While TailCalls do return some values, those values are returned to the
4238 // caller rather than to the current function (and a TailCallOp thus never
4239 // has any uses), so we set the outputs_rep to empty. If you need to know
4240 // what a TailCallOp returns, you can find out in `descriptor->outputs_rep`.
4241 return {};
4242 }
4243
4244 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
4245 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
4246 storage.resize(input_count);
4247 size_t i = 0;
4248#ifdef V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4249 if (descriptor->descriptor->IsIndirectWasmFunctionCall()) {
4250 storage[i++] = MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Word32();
4251 } else if (descriptor->descriptor->IsDirectWasmFunctionCall() ||
4252 descriptor->descriptor->IsWasmImportWrapper() ||
4253 descriptor->descriptor->IsWasmCapiFunction()) {
4254 storage[i++] = MaybeRegisterRepresentation::WordPtr();
4255 } else {
4256 storage[i++] = MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged();
4257 }
4258#else
4259 storage[i++] = MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged();
4260#endif
4261 for (auto rep : descriptor->in_reps) {
4262 storage[i++] = rep;
4263 }
4264 storage.resize(i);
4265 return base::VectorOf(storage);
4266 }
4267
4268 OpIndex callee() const { return input(0); }
4269 base::Vector<const OpIndex> arguments() const {
4270 return inputs().SubVector(1, input_count);
4271 }
4272
4273 TailCallOp(OpIndex callee, base::Vector<const OpIndex> arguments,
4274 const TSCallDescriptor* descriptor)
4275 : Base(1 + arguments.size()), descriptor(descriptor) {
4276 base::Vector<OpIndex> inputs = this->inputs();
4277 inputs[0] = callee;
4278 inputs.SubVector(1, inputs.size()).OverwriteWith(arguments);
4279 }
4280
4281 template <typename Fn, typename Mapper>
4282 V8_INLINE auto Explode(Fn fn, Mapper& mapper) const {
4283 OpIndex mapped_callee = mapper.Map(callee());
4284 auto mapped_arguments = mapper.template Map<16>(arguments());
4285 return fn(mapped_callee, base::VectorOf(mapped_arguments), descriptor);
4286 }
4287
4288 static TailCallOp& New(Graph* graph, OpIndex callee,
4289 base::Vector<const OpIndex> arguments,
4290 const TSCallDescriptor* descriptor) {
4291 return Base::New(graph, 1 + arguments.size(), callee, arguments,
4292 descriptor);
4293 }
4294 auto options() const { return std::tuple{descriptor}; }
4295 void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;
4296};

4313struct ReturnOp : OperationT<ReturnOp> {
4314 // spill_caller_frame_slots signals that all caller stack located return
4315 // values should be spilled before reaching the InstructionSelector.
4316 // The growable stacks implementation does extra work to spill these values
4317 // and it cannot be performed during InstructionSelector lowering efficiently.
4318 bool spill_caller_frame_slots;
4319 static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects().CanLeaveCurrentFunction();
4320 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const { return {}; }
4321
4322 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
4323 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
4324 // TODO(mliedtke): Ideally, a return op would expect to get the correct
4325 // types for all its return values, not just the pop count.
4326 return MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Word32()>();
4327 }
4328
4329 // Number of additional stack slots to be removed.
4330 V<Word32> pop_count() const { return input<Word32>(0); }
4331
4332 base::Vector<const OpIndex> return_values() const {
4333 return inputs().SubVector(1, input_count);
4334 }
4335
4336 ReturnOp(V<Word32> pop_count, base::Vector<const OpIndex> return_values,
4337 bool spill_caller_frame_slots)
4338 : Base(1 + return_values.size()),
4339 spill_caller_frame_slots(spill_caller_frame_slots) {
4340 base::Vector<OpIndex> inputs = this->inputs();
4341 inputs[0] = pop_count;
4342 inputs.SubVector(1, inputs.size()).OverwriteWith(return_values);
4343 }
4344
4345 template <typename Fn, typename Mapper>
4346 V8_INLINE auto Explode(Fn fn, Mapper& mapper) const {
4347 OpIndex mapped_pop_count = mapper.Map(pop_count());
4348 auto mapped_return_values = mapper.template Map<4>(return_values());
4349 return fn(mapped_pop_count, base::VectorOf(mapped_return_values),
4350 spill_caller_frame_slots);
4351 }
4352
4353 static ReturnOp& New(Graph* graph, V<Word32> pop_count,
4354 base::Vector<const OpIndex> return_values,
4355 bool spill_caller_frame_slots) {
4356 return Base::New(graph, 1 + return_values.size(), pop_count, return_values,
4357 spill_caller_frame_slots);
4358 }
4359 auto options() const { return std::tuple{spill_caller_frame_slots}; }
4360};

4403struct SwitchOp : FixedArityOperationT<1, SwitchOp> {
4404 struct Case {
4405 BranchHint hint;
4406 int32_t value;
4407 Block* destination;
4408
4409 Case(int32_t value, Block* destination, BranchHint hint)
4410 : hint(hint), value(value), destination(destination) {}
4411
4412 bool operator==(const Case& other) const {
4413 return value == other.value && destination == other.destination &&
4414 hint == other.hint;
4415 }
4416 };
4417 BranchHint default_hint;
4418 base::Vector<Case> cases;
4419 Block* default_case;
4420
4421 static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects().CanChangeControlFlow();
4422 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const { return {}; }
4423
4424 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
4425 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
4426 return MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Word32()>();
4427 }
4428
4429 V<Word32> input() const { return Base::input<Word32>(0); }
4430
4431 SwitchOp(V<Word32> input, base::Vector<Case> cases, Block* default_case,
4432 BranchHint default_hint)
4433 : Base(input),
4434 default_hint(default_hint),
4435 cases(cases),
4436 default_case(default_case) {}
4437
4438 void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;
4439 size_t hash_value(HashingStrategy strategy = HashingStrategy::kDefault) const;
4440 auto options() const { return std::tuple{cases, default_case, default_hint}; }
4441};
4442
4443template <>
4444struct fast_hash<SwitchOp::Case> {
4445 size_t operator()(SwitchOp::Case v) {
4446 return fast_hash_combine(v.value, v.destination);
4447 }
4448};
4449
4450inline base::SmallVector<Block*, 4> SuccessorBlocks(const Operation& op) {
4451 switch (op.opcode) {
4452 case Opcode::kCheckException: {
4453 auto& casted = op.Cast<CheckExceptionOp>();
4454 return {casted.didnt_throw_block, casted.catch_block};
4455 }
4456 case Opcode::kGoto: {
4457 auto& casted = op.Cast<GotoOp>();
4458 return {casted.destination};
4459 }
4460 case Opcode::kBranch: {
4461 auto& casted = op.Cast<BranchOp>();
4462 return {casted.if_true, casted.if_false};
4463 }
4464 case Opcode::kReturn:
4465 case Opcode::kTailCall:
4466 case Opcode::kDeoptimize:
4467 case Opcode::kUnreachable:
4468 return base::SmallVector<Block*, 4>{};
4469 case Opcode::kSwitch: {
4470 auto& casted = op.Cast<SwitchOp>();
4471 base::SmallVector<Block*, 4> result;
4472 for (const SwitchOp::Case& c : casted.cases) {
4473 result.push_back(c.destination);
4474 }
4475 result.push_back(casted.default_case);
4476 return result;
4477 }
4478#define NON_TERMINATOR_CASE(op) case Opcode::k##op:
4479 TURBOSHAFT_OPERATION_LIST_NOT_BLOCK_TERMINATOR(NON_TERMINATOR_CASE)
4480 UNREACHABLE();
4481#undef NON_TERMINATOR_CASE
4482 }
4483}
4484
4485V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE base::SmallVector<Block*, 4> SuccessorBlocks(
4486 const Block& block, const Graph& graph);
4487
4488// Tuples are only used to lower operations with multiple outputs.
4489// `TupleOp` should be folded away by subsequent `ProjectionOp`s.
4490struct TupleOp : OperationT<TupleOp> {
4491 static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects();
4492 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const { return {}; }
4493
4494 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
4495 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
4496 return {};
4497 }
4498
4499 explicit TupleOp(base::Vector<const V<Any>> inputs) : Base(inputs) {}
4500
4501 template <typename Fn, typename Mapper>
4502 V8_INLINE auto Explode(Fn fn, Mapper& mapper) const {
4503 auto mapped_inputs = mapper.template Map<4>(inputs());
4504 return fn(base::VectorOf(mapped_inputs));
4505 }
4506
4507 auto options() const { return std::tuple{}; }
4508};

4510// For operations that produce multiple results, we use `ProjectionOp` to
4511// distinguish them.
4512struct ProjectionOp : FixedArityOperationT<1, ProjectionOp> {
4513 uint16_t index;
4514 RegisterRepresentation rep;
4515
4516 static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects();
4517 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
4518 return base::VectorOf(&rep, 1);
4519 }
4520
4521 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
4522 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
4523 return {};
4524 }
4525
4526 V<Any> input() const { return Base::input<Any>(0); }
4527
4528 ProjectionOp(V<Any> input, uint16_t index, RegisterRepresentation rep)
4529 : Base(input), index(index), rep(rep) {}
4530
4531 void Validate(const Graph& graph) const {
4532 DCHECK(ValidOpInputRep(graph, input(), rep, index));
4533 }
4534 auto options() const { return std::tuple{index, rep}; }
4535};

4718struct ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp
4719 : FixedArityOperationT<1, ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp> {
4720 enum class JSPrimitiveKind : uint8_t {
4721 kBigInt,
4722 kBoolean,
4723 kHeapNumber,
4724 kHeapNumberOrUndefined,
4725 kNumber,
4726 kSmi,
4727 kString,
4728 };
4729 enum class InputInterpretation : uint8_t {
4730 kSigned,
4731 kUnsigned,
4732 kCharCode,
4733 kCodePoint,
4734 };
4735 JSPrimitiveKind kind;
4736 RegisterRepresentation input_rep;
4737 InputInterpretation input_interpretation;
4738 CheckForMinusZeroMode minus_zero_mode;
4739
4740 // The input is untagged and the results are identityless primitives.
4741 static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects().CanAllocateWithoutIdentity();
4742 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
4743 return RepVector<RegisterRepresentation::Tagged()>();
4744 }
4745
4746 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
4747 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
4748 return InputsRepFactory::SingleRep(input_rep);
4749 }
4750
4751 V<Untagged> input() const { return Base::input<Untagged>(0); }
4752
4753 ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp(V<Untagged> input, JSPrimitiveKind kind,
4754 RegisterRepresentation input_rep,
4755 InputInterpretation input_interpretation,
4756 CheckForMinusZeroMode minus_zero_mode)
4757 : Base(input),
4758 kind(kind),
4759 input_rep(input_rep),
4760 input_interpretation(input_interpretation),
4761 minus_zero_mode(minus_zero_mode) {}
4762
4763 void Validate(const Graph& graph) const {
4764 switch (kind) {
4765 case JSPrimitiveKind::kBigInt:
4766 DCHECK_EQ(input_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Word64());
4767 DCHECK_EQ(minus_zero_mode,
4768 CheckForMinusZeroMode::kDontCheckForMinusZero);
4769 break;
4770 case JSPrimitiveKind::kBoolean:
4771 DCHECK_EQ(input_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Word32());
4772 DCHECK_EQ(minus_zero_mode,
4773 CheckForMinusZeroMode::kDontCheckForMinusZero);
4774 break;
4775 case JSPrimitiveKind::kNumber:
4776 case JSPrimitiveKind::kHeapNumber:
4777 DCHECK_IMPLIES(
4778 minus_zero_mode == CheckForMinusZeroMode::kCheckForMinusZero,
4779 input_rep == RegisterRepresentation::Float64());
4780 break;
4781 case JSPrimitiveKind::kHeapNumberOrUndefined:
4782 DCHECK_IMPLIES(
4783 minus_zero_mode == CheckForMinusZeroMode::kDontCheckForMinusZero,
4784 input_rep == RegisterRepresentation::Float64());
4785 break;
4786 case JSPrimitiveKind::kSmi:
4787 DCHECK_EQ(input_rep, WordRepresentation::Word32());
4788 DCHECK_EQ(minus_zero_mode,
4789 CheckForMinusZeroMode::kDontCheckForMinusZero);
4790 break;
4791 case JSPrimitiveKind::kString:
4792 DCHECK_EQ(input_rep, WordRepresentation::Word32());
4793 DCHECK_EQ(input_interpretation,
4794 any_of(InputInterpretation::kCharCode,
4795 InputInterpretation::kCodePoint));
4796 break;
4797 }
4798 }
4799
4800 auto options() const {
4801 return std::tuple{kind, input_rep, input_interpretation, minus_zero_mode};
4802 }
4803};
4804V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE std::ostream& operator<<(
4805 std::ostream& os, ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind kind);

5092

5211// TODO(nicohartmann@): We should consider getting rid of the LoadFieldByIndex
5212// operation.
5213struct LoadFieldByIndexOp : FixedArityOperationT<2, LoadFieldByIndexOp> {
5214 static constexpr OpEffects effects =
5215 OpEffects()
5216 // Read the possibly mutable property.
5217 .CanReadHeapMemory()
5218 // We may allocate heap number for the result.
5219 .CanAllocateWithoutIdentity()
5220 // We assume the input is an object.
5221 .CanDependOnChecks();
5222 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
5223 return RepVector<RegisterRepresentation::Tagged()>();
5224 }
5225
5226 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
5227 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
5228 return MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged(),
5229 MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Word32()>();
5230 }
5231
5232 OpIndex object() const { return Base::input(0); }
5233 // Index encoding (see `src/objects/field-index-inl.h`):
5234 // For efficiency, the LoadByFieldIndex instruction takes an index that is
5235 // optimized for quick access. If the property is inline, the index is
5236 // positive. If it's out-of-line, the encoded index is -raw_index - 1 to
5237 // disambiguate the zero out-of-line index from the zero inobject case.
5238 // The index itself is shifted up by one bit, the lower-most bit
5239 // signifying if the field is a mutable double box (1) or not (0).
5240 OpIndex index() const { return Base::input(1); }
5241
5242 LoadFieldByIndexOp(OpIndex object, OpIndex index) : Base(object, index) {}
5243
5244 auto options() const { return std::tuple{}; }
5245};

5262struct DebugPrintOp : FixedArityOperationT<1, DebugPrintOp> {
5263 RegisterRepresentation rep;
5264
5265 // We just need to ensure that the debug print stays in the same block and
5266 // observes the right memory state. It doesn't actually change control flow,
5267 // but pretending so ensures the we do not remove the debug print even though
5268 // it is unused. We assume that the debug print doesn't affect memory so that
5269 // the scheduling of loads is not affected.
5270 static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects()
5271 .CanChangeControlFlow()
5272 .CanDependOnChecks()
5273 .CanReadMemory()
5274 .RequiredWhenUnused();
5275 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const { return {}; }
5276
5277 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
5278 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
5279 return InputsRepFactory::SingleRep(rep);
5280 }
5281
5282 OpIndex input() const { return Base::input(0); }
5283
5284 DebugPrintOp(OpIndex input, RegisterRepresentation rep)
5285 : Base(input), rep(rep) {}
5286
5287 auto options() const { return std::tuple{rep}; }
5288};

5732
5733inline constexpr RegisterRepresentation RegisterRepresentationForArrayType(
5734 ExternalArrayType array_type) {
5735 switch (array_type) {
5736 case kExternalInt8Array:
5737 case kExternalUint8Array:
5738 case kExternalUint8ClampedArray:
5739 case kExternalInt16Array:
5740 case kExternalUint16Array:
5741 case kExternalInt32Array:
5742 case kExternalUint32Array:
5743 return RegisterRepresentation::Word32();
5744 case kExternalFloat32Array:
5745 return RegisterRepresentation::Float32();
5746 case kExternalFloat64Array:
5747 return RegisterRepresentation::Float64();
5748 case kExternalBigInt64Array:
5749 case kExternalBigUint64Array:
5750 return RegisterRepresentation::Word64();
5751 case kExternalFloat16Array:
5752 UNIMPLEMENTED();
5753 }
5754}
5755
5756inline base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> VectorForRep(
5757 RegisterRepresentation rep) {
5758 static constexpr std::array<RegisterRepresentation, 6> table{
5759 RegisterRepresentation::Word32(), RegisterRepresentation::Word64(),
5760 RegisterRepresentation::Float32(), RegisterRepresentation::Float64(),
5761 RegisterRepresentation::Tagged(), RegisterRepresentation::Compressed()};
5762 return base::VectorOf(&table[static_cast<size_t>(rep.value())], 1);
5763}

5766 ExternalArrayType array_type;
5767
5768 static constexpr OpEffects effects =
5769 OpEffects()
5770 // We read mutable memory.
5771 .CanReadMemory()
5772 // We rely on the input type and a valid index.
5773 .CanDependOnChecks();
5774 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
5775 return VectorForRep(RegisterRepresentationForArrayType(array_type));
5776 }
5777
5778 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
5779 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
5780 return MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged(),
5781 MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged(),
5782 MaybeRegisterRepresentation::WordPtr(),
5783 MaybeRegisterRepresentation::WordPtr()>();
5784 }
5785
5786 OpIndex buffer() const { return Base::input(0); }
5787 OpIndex base() const { return Base::input(1); }
5788 OpIndex external() const { return Base::input(2); }
5789 OpIndex index() const { return Base::input(3); }
5790
5791 LoadTypedElementOp(OpIndex buffer, OpIndex base, OpIndex external,
5792 OpIndex index, ExternalArrayType array_type)
5793 : Base(buffer, base, external, index), array_type(array_type) {}
5794
5795
5796 auto options() const { return std::tuple{array_type}; }
5797};

5933
5934struct TransitionAndStoreArrayElementOp
5935 : FixedArityOperationT<3, TransitionAndStoreArrayElementOp> {
5936 enum class Kind : uint8_t {
5937 kElement,
5938 kNumberElement,
5939 kOddballElement,
5940 kNonNumberElement,
5941 kSignedSmallElement,
5942 };
5943 Kind kind;
5944 MaybeIndirectHandle<Map> fast_map;
5945 MaybeIndirectHandle<Map> double_map;
5946
5947 static constexpr OpEffects effects =
5948 OpEffects()
5949 // We are reading and writing mutable memory.
5950 .CanReadHeapMemory()
5951 .CanWriteHeapMemory()
5952 // We rely on the input type and a valid index.
5953 .CanDependOnChecks();
5954 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const { return {}; }
5955
5956 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
5957 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
5958 return InitVectorOf(
5959 storage, {RegisterRepresentation::Tagged(),
5960 RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr(), value_representation()});
5961 }
5962
5963 V<JSArray> array() const { return Base::input<JSArray>(0); }
5964 V<WordPtr> index() const { return Base::input<WordPtr>(1); }
5965 V<Any> value() const { return Base::input<Any>(2); }
5966
5967 TransitionAndStoreArrayElementOp(V<JSArray> array, V<WordPtr> index,
5968 V<Any> value, Kind kind,
5969 MaybeIndirectHandle<Map> fast_map,
5970 MaybeIndirectHandle<Map> double_map)
5971 : Base(array, index, value),
5972 kind(kind),
5973 fast_map(fast_map),
5974 double_map(double_map) {}
5975
5976
5977 RegisterRepresentation value_representation() const {
5978 switch (kind) {
5979 case Kind::kElement:
5980 case Kind::kNonNumberElement:
5981 case Kind::kOddballElement:
5982 return RegisterRepresentation::Tagged();
5983 case Kind::kNumberElement:
5984 return RegisterRepresentation::Float64();
5985 case Kind::kSignedSmallElement:
5986 return RegisterRepresentation::Word32();
5987 }
5988 }
5989
5990 size_t hash_value(
5991 HashingStrategy strategy = HashingStrategy::kDefault) const {
5992 DCHECK_EQ(strategy, HashingStrategy::kDefault);
5993 return HashWithOptions(fast_map.address(), double_map.address());
5994 }
5995
5996 bool operator==(const TransitionAndStoreArrayElementOp& other) const {
5997 return kind == other.kind && fast_map.equals(other.fast_map) &&
5998 double_map.equals(other.double_map);
5999 }
6000
6001 auto options() const { return std::tuple{kind, fast_map, double_map}; }
6002};
6003
6004V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE std::ostream& operator<<(
6005 std::ostream& os, TransitionAndStoreArrayElementOp::Kind kind);
