6007struct CompareMapsOp : OperationT<CompareMapsOp> {
6008 ZoneRefSet<Map> maps;
6009
6010 static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects().CanReadHeapMemory();
6011 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
6012 return RepVector<RegisterRepresentation::Word32()>();
6013 }
6014
6015 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
6016 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
6017 return MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged()>();
6018 }
6019
6020 V<HeapObject> heap_object() const { return Base::input<HeapObject>(0); }
6021
6022 OptionalV<Map> map() const {
6023 return input_count > 1 ? input<Map>(1) : OptionalV<Map>::Nullopt();
6024 }
6025
6026 CompareMapsOp(V<HeapObject> heap_object, OptionalV<Map> map,
6027 ZoneRefSet<Map> maps)
6028 : Base(1 + map.valid()), maps(std::move(maps)) {
6029 input(0) = heap_object;
6030 if (map.valid()) {
6031 input(1) = map.value();
6032 }
6033 }
6034
6035
6036 auto options() const { return std::tuple{maps}; }
6037 void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;
6038
6039 template <typename Fn, typename Mapper>
6040 V8_INLINE auto Explode(Fn fn, Mapper& mapper) const {
6041 return fn(mapper.Map(heap_object()), mapper.Map(map()), maps);
6042 }
6043
6044 static CompareMapsOp& New(Graph* graph, V<HeapObject> heap_object,
6045 OptionalV<Map> map, ZoneRefSet<Map> maps) {
6046 return Base::New(graph, 1 + map.valid(), heap_object, map, maps);
6047 }
6048};
6049
6050struct CheckMapsOp : OperationT<CheckMapsOp> {
6051 CheckMapsFlags flags;
6052 ZoneRefSet<Map> maps;
6053 FeedbackSource feedback;
6054
6055 // TODO(tebbi): Map checks without map transitions have less effects.
6056 static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects()
6057 .CanDependOnChecks()
6058 .CanDeopt()
6059 .CanReadHeapMemory()
6060 .CanWriteHeapMemory();
6061 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const { return {}; }
6062
6063 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
6064 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
6065 return MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged()>();
6066 }
6067
6068 V<HeapObject> heap_object() const { return Base::input<HeapObject>(0); }
6069 V<FrameState> frame_state() const { return Base::input<FrameState>(1); }
6070 OptionalV<Map> map() const {
6071 return input_count > 2 ? input<Map>(2) : OptionalV<Map>::Nullopt();
6072 }
6073
6074 CheckMapsOp(V<HeapObject> heap_object, V<FrameState> frame_state,
6075 OptionalV<Map> map, ZoneRefSet<Map> maps, CheckMapsFlags flags,
6076 const FeedbackSource& feedback)
6077 : Base(2 + map.valid()),
6078 flags(flags),
6079 maps(std::move(maps)),
6080 feedback(feedback) {
6081 input(0) = heap_object;
6082 input(1) = frame_state;
6083 if (map.valid()) {
6084 input(2) = map.value();
6085 }
6086 }
6087
6088 void Validate(const Graph& graph) const {
6089 DCHECK(Get(graph, frame_state()).Is<FrameStateOp>());
6090 }
6091
6092 auto options() const { return std::tuple{maps, flags, feedback}; }
6093 void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;
6094
6095 template <typename Fn, typename Mapper>
6096 V8_INLINE auto Explode(Fn fn, Mapper& mapper) const {
6097 return fn(mapper.Map(heap_object()), mapper.Map(frame_state()),
6098 mapper.Map(map()), maps, flags, feedback);
6099 }
6100
6101 static CheckMapsOp& New(Graph* graph, V<HeapObject> heap_object,
6102 V<FrameState> frame_state, OptionalV<Map> map,
6103 ZoneRefSet<Map> maps, CheckMapsFlags flags,
6104 const FeedbackSource& feedback) {
6105 return Base::New(graph, 2 + map.valid(), heap_object, frame_state, map,
6106 maps, flags, feedback);
6107 }
6108};
6109
6110// AssumeMaps are inserted after CheckMaps have been lowered, in order to keep
6111// map information around and easily accessible for subsequent optimization
6112// passes (Load Elimination for instance can then use those AssumeMap to
6113// determine that some objects don't alias because they have different maps).
6114struct AssumeMapOp : FixedArityOperationT<1, AssumeMapOp> {
6115 ZoneRefSet<Map> maps;
6116 // AssumeMap should not be scheduled before the preceding CheckMaps
6117 static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects()
6118 .CanDependOnChecks()
6119 .CanReadHeapMemory()
6120 .CanChangeControlFlow();
6121 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const { return {}; }
6122
6123 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
6124 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
6125 return MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged()>();
6126 }
6127
6128 V<HeapObject> heap_object() const { return Base::input<HeapObject>(0); }
6129
6130 AssumeMapOp(V<HeapObject> heap_object, ZoneRefSet<Map> maps)
6131 : Base(heap_object), maps(std::move(maps)) {}
6132
6133
6134 auto options() const { return std::tuple{maps}; }
6135 void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;
6136};

6300struct FastApiCallParameters : public NON_EXPORTED_BASE(ZoneObject) {
6301 FastApiCallFunction c_function;
6302
6303 const CFunctionInfo* c_signature() const { return c_function.signature; }
6304
6305 explicit FastApiCallParameters(FastApiCallFunction c_function)
6306 : c_function(c_function) {}
6307
6308 static const FastApiCallParameters* Create(FastApiCallFunction c_function,
6309 Zone* graph_zone) {
6310 return graph_zone->New<FastApiCallParameters>(c_function);
6311 }
6312};
6313
6314struct FastApiCallOp : OperationT<FastApiCallOp> {
6315 static constexpr uint32_t kSuccessValue = 1;
6316 static constexpr uint32_t kFailureValue = 0;
6317
6318 const FastApiCallParameters* parameters;
6319 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> out_reps;
6320 LazyDeoptOnThrow lazy_deopt_on_throw;
6321
6322 static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects().CanCallAnything();
6323
6324 // There are three inputs that are not parameters, the frame state, the data
6325 // argument, and the context.
6326 static constexpr int kNumNonParamInputs = 3;
6327
6328 // The outputs are produced by the `DidntThrow` operation.
6329 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const { return {}; }
6330
6331 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
6332 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
6333 DCHECK_EQ(inputs().size(),
6334 kNumNonParamInputs + parameters->c_signature()->ArgumentCount());
6335 storage.resize(inputs().size());
6336 storage[0] = MaybeRegisterRepresentation::None();
6337 storage[1] = MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged();
6338 storage[2] = MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged();
6339 for (unsigned i = 0; i < parameters->c_signature()->ArgumentCount(); ++i) {
6340 storage[i + kNumNonParamInputs] = argument_representation(i);
6341 }
6342 return base::VectorOf(storage);
6343 }
6344
6345 MaybeRegisterRepresentation argument_representation(
6346 unsigned argument_index) const {
6347 const CTypeInfo& arg_type =
6348 parameters->c_signature()->ArgumentInfo(argument_index);
6349 uint8_t flags = static_cast<uint8_t>(arg_type.GetFlags());
6350 START_ALLOW_USE_DEPRECATED()
6351 switch (arg_type.GetSequenceType()) {
6352 case CTypeInfo::SequenceType::kScalar:
6353 if (flags & (static_cast<uint8_t>(CTypeInfo::Flags::kEnforceRangeBit) |
6354 static_cast<uint8_t>(CTypeInfo::Flags::kClampBit))) {
6355 return MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Float64();
6356 }
6357 switch (arg_type.GetType()) {
6358 case CTypeInfo::Type::kVoid:
6359 UNREACHABLE();
6360 case CTypeInfo::Type::kBool:
6361 case CTypeInfo::Type::kUint8:
6362 case CTypeInfo::Type::kInt32:
6363 case CTypeInfo::Type::kUint32:
6364 return MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Word32();
6365 case CTypeInfo::Type::kInt64:
6366 case CTypeInfo::Type::kUint64:
6367 return MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Word64();
6368 case CTypeInfo::Type::kV8Value:
6369 case CTypeInfo::Type::kApiObject:
6370 case CTypeInfo::Type::kPointer:
6371 case CTypeInfo::Type::kSeqOneByteString:
6372 return MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged();
6373 case CTypeInfo::Type::kFloat32:
6374 case CTypeInfo::Type::kFloat64:
6375 return MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Float64();
6376 case CTypeInfo::Type::kAny:
6377 // As the register representation is unknown, just treat it as None
6378 // to prevent any validation.
6379 return MaybeRegisterRepresentation::None();
6380 }
6381 case CTypeInfo::SequenceType::kIsSequence:
6382 case CTypeInfo::SequenceType::kIsTypedArray:
6383 return MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged();
6384 case CTypeInfo::SequenceType::kIsArrayBuffer:
6385 UNREACHABLE();
6386 }
6387 END_ALLOW_USE_DEPRECATED()
6388 }
6389
6390 V<FrameState> frame_state() const { return input<FrameState>(0); }
6391
6392 V<Object> data_argument() const { return input<Object>(1); }
6393
6394 V<Context> context() const { return input<Context>(2); }
6395
6396 base::Vector<const OpIndex> arguments() const {
6397 return inputs().SubVector(kNumNonParamInputs, inputs().size());
6398 }
6399
6400 FastApiCallOp(V<FrameState> frame_state, V<Object> data_argument,
6401 V<Context> context, base::Vector<const OpIndex> arguments,
6402 const FastApiCallParameters* parameters,
6403 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> out_reps)
6404 : Base(kNumNonParamInputs + arguments.size()),
6405 parameters(parameters),
6406 out_reps(out_reps),
6407 lazy_deopt_on_throw(LazyDeoptOnThrow::kNo) {
6408 base::Vector<OpIndex> inputs = this->inputs();
6409 inputs[0] = frame_state;
6410 inputs[1] = data_argument;
6411 inputs[2] = context;
6412 inputs.SubVector(kNumNonParamInputs, kNumNonParamInputs + arguments.size())
6413 .OverwriteWith(arguments);
6414 }
6415
6416 template <typename Fn, typename Mapper>
6417 V8_INLINE auto Explode(Fn fn, Mapper& mapper) const {
6418 V<FrameState> mapped_frame_state = mapper.Map(frame_state());
6419 OpIndex mapped_data_argument = mapper.Map(data_argument());
6420 V<Context> mapped_context = mapper.Map(context());
6421 auto mapped_arguments = mapper.template Map<8>(arguments());
6422 return fn(mapped_frame_state, mapped_data_argument, mapped_context,
6423 base::VectorOf(mapped_arguments), parameters, out_reps);
6424 }
6425
6426
6427 static FastApiCallOp& New(
6428 Graph* graph, V<FrameState> frame_state, V<Object> data_argument,
6429 V<Context> context, base::Vector<const OpIndex> arguments,
6430 const FastApiCallParameters* parameters,
6431 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> out_reps) {
6432 return Base::New(graph, kNumNonParamInputs + arguments.size(), frame_state,
6433 data_argument, context, arguments, parameters, out_reps);
6434 }
6435
6436 // out_reps[0] is always word32.
6437 auto options() const {
6438 DCHECK_EQ(out_reps[0], RegisterRepresentation::Word32());
6439 return std::tuple{parameters, out_reps[1], lazy_deopt_on_throw};
6440 }
6441};

6568struct FindOrderedHashEntryOp
6569 : FixedArityOperationT<2, FindOrderedHashEntryOp> {
6570 enum class Kind : uint8_t {
6571 kFindOrderedHashMapEntry,
6572 kFindOrderedHashMapEntryForInt32Key,
6573 kFindOrderedHashSetEntry,
6574 };
6575 Kind kind;
6576
6577 static constexpr OpEffects effects =
6578 OpEffects().CanDependOnChecks().CanReadMemory().CanAllocate();
6579 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
6580 switch (kind) {
6581 case Kind::kFindOrderedHashMapEntry:
6582 case Kind::kFindOrderedHashSetEntry:
6583 return RepVector<RegisterRepresentation::Tagged()>();
6584 case Kind::kFindOrderedHashMapEntryForInt32Key:
6585 return RepVector<RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr()>();
6586 }
6587 }
6588
6589 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
6590 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
6591 return kind == Kind::kFindOrderedHashMapEntryForInt32Key
6592 ? MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged(),
6593 MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Word32()>()
6594 : MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged(),
6595 MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged()>();
6596 }
6597
6598 OpIndex data_structure() const { return Base::input(0); }
6599 V<Word32> key() const { return Base::input<Word32>(1); }
6600
6601 FindOrderedHashEntryOp(OpIndex data_structure, V<Word32> key, Kind kind)
6602 : Base(data_structure, key), kind(kind) {}
6603
6604
6605 auto options() const { return std::tuple{kind}; }
6606};
6607V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os,
6608 FindOrderedHashEntryOp::Kind kind);

6823struct WasmTypeCheckOp : OperationT<WasmTypeCheckOp> {
6824 WasmTypeCheckConfig config;
6825
6826 static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects().AssumesConsistentHeap();
6827
6828 WasmTypeCheckOp(V<Object> object, OptionalV<Map> rtt,
6829 WasmTypeCheckConfig config)
6830 : Base(1 + rtt.valid()), config(config) {
6831 input(0) = object;
6832 if (rtt.valid()) {
6833 input(1) = rtt.value();
6834 }
6835 }
6836
6837 template <typename Fn, typename Mapper>
6838 V8_INLINE auto Explode(Fn fn, Mapper& mapper) const {
6839 return fn(mapper.Map(object()), mapper.Map(rtt()), config);
6840 }
6841
6842 V<Object> object() const { return Base::input<Object>(0); }
6843 OptionalV<Map> rtt() const {
6844 return input_count > 1 ? input<Map>(1) : OptionalV<Map>::Nullopt();
6845 }
6846
6847 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
6848 return RepVector<RegisterRepresentation::Word32()>();
6849 }
6850
6851 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
6852 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
6853 return input_count > 1
6854 ? MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged(),
6855 MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged()>()
6856 : MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged()>();
6857 }
6858
6859
6860 auto options() const { return std::tuple{config}; }
6861
6862 static WasmTypeCheckOp& New(Graph* graph, V<Object> object,
6863 OptionalV<Map> rtt, WasmTypeCheckConfig config) {
6864 return Base::New(graph, 1 + rtt.valid(), object, rtt, config);
6865 }
6866};

6986struct StructGetOp : FixedArityOperationT<1, StructGetOp> {
6987 bool is_signed; // `false` only for unsigned packed type accesses.
6988 CheckForNull null_check;
6989 const wasm::StructType* type;
6990 wasm::ModuleTypeIndex type_index;
6991 int field_index;
6992
6993 OpEffects Effects() const {
6994 OpEffects result =
6995 OpEffects()
6996 // This should not float above a protective null check.
6997 .CanDependOnChecks()
6998 .CanReadMemory();
6999 if (null_check == kWithNullCheck) {
7000 // This may trap.
7001 result = result.CanLeaveCurrentFunction();
7002 }
7003 return result;
7004 }
7005
7006 StructGetOp(V<WasmStructNullable> object, const wasm::StructType* type,
7007 wasm::ModuleTypeIndex type_index, int field_index, bool is_signed,
7008 CheckForNull null_check)
7009 : Base(object),
7010 is_signed(is_signed),
7011 null_check(null_check),
7012 type(type),
7013 type_index(type_index),
7014 field_index(field_index) {}
7015
7016 V<WasmStructNullable> object() const { return input<WasmStructNullable>(0); }
7017
7018 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
7019 return base::VectorOf(&RepresentationFor(type->field(field_index)), 1);
7020 }
7021
7022 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
7023 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
7024 return MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged()>();
7025 }
7026
7027 void Validate(const Graph& graph) const {
7028 DCHECK_LT(field_index, type->field_count());
7029 DCHECK_IMPLIES(!is_signed, type->field(field_index).is_packed());
7030 }
7031
7032 auto options() const {
7033 return std::tuple{type, type_index, field_index, is_signed, null_check};
7034 }
7035};

7038 CheckForNull null_check;

7042
7043 OpEffects Effects() const {
7044 OpEffects result =
7045 OpEffects()
7046 // This should not float above a protective null check.
7047 .CanDependOnChecks()
7048 .CanWriteMemory();
7049 if (null_check == kWithNullCheck) {
7050 // This may trap.
7051 result = result.CanLeaveCurrentFunction();

7053 return result;
7054 }
7055
7056 StructSetOp(V<WasmStructNullable> object, V<Any> value,

7064
7065 V<WasmStructNullable> object() const { return input<WasmStructNullable>(0); }
7066 V<Any> value() const { return input(1); }
7067
7068 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const { return {}; }
7069
7070 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
7071 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
7072 storage.resize(2);
7073 storage[0] = RegisterRepresentation::Tagged();
7074 storage[1] = RepresentationFor(type->field(field_index));
7075 return base::VectorOf(storage);
7076 }
7077
7078 void Validate(const Graph& graph) const {
7079 DCHECK_LT(field_index, type->field_count());
7080 }
7081
7082 auto options() const {
7083 return std::tuple{type, type_index, field_index, null_check};
7084 }
7085};

7093 OpEffects()
7094 // This should not float above a protective null/length check.
7095 .CanDependOnChecks()
7096 .CanReadMemory();
7097
7098 ArrayGetOp(V<WasmArrayNullable> array, V<Word32> index,

7151struct ArrayLengthOp : FixedArityOperationT<1, ArrayLengthOp> {
7152 CheckForNull null_check;
7153
7154 OpEffects Effects() const {
7155 OpEffects result =
7156 OpEffects()
7157 // This should not float above a protective null check.
7158 .CanDependOnChecks()
7159 .CanReadMemory();
7160 if (null_check == kWithNullCheck) {
7161 // This may trap.
7162 result = result.CanLeaveCurrentFunction();
7163 }
7164 return result;
7165 }
7166
7167 explicit ArrayLengthOp(V<WasmArrayNullable> array, CheckForNull null_check)
7168 : Base(array), null_check(null_check) {}
7169
7170 V<WasmArrayNullable> array() const { return input<WasmArrayNullable>(0); }
7171
7172 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
7173 return RepVector<RegisterRepresentation::Word32()>();
7174 }
7175
7176 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
7177 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
7178 return MaybeRepVector<RegisterRepresentation::Tagged()>();
7179 }
7180
7181
7182 auto options() const { return std::tuple{null_check}; }
7183};

7312struct Simd128ConstantOp : FixedArityOperationT<0, Simd128ConstantOp> {

7316 static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects();

7318 explicit Simd128ConstantOp(const uint8_t incoming_value[kSimd128Size])
7319 : Base() {
7320 std::copy(incoming_value, incoming_value + kSimd128Size, value);
7321 }
7322
7323 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
7324 return RepVector<RegisterRepresentation::Simd128()>();
7325 }
7326

7328 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
7329 return {};
7330 }
7331
7332 void Validate(const Graph& graph) const {
7333 // TODO(14108): Validate.
7334 }
7335

7337
7338 auto options() const { return std::tuple{value}; }
7339 void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;
7340};

7480struct Simd128BinopOp : FixedArityOperationT<2, Simd128BinopOp> {
7481 // clang-format off
7482 enum class Kind : uint8_t {
7483#define DEFINE_KIND(kind) k##kind,
7484 FOREACH_SIMD_128_BINARY_OPCODE(DEFINE_KIND)
7485 kFirstSignExtensionOp = kI16x8ExtMulLowI8x16S,
7486 kLastSignExtensionOp = kI64x2ExtMulHighI32x4U,
7487#undef DEFINE_KIND
7488 };
7489 // clang-format on
7490
7491 Kind kind;
7492
7493 static bool IsCommutative(Kind kind) {
7494 switch (kind) {
7495 // TODO(14108): Explicitly list all commutative SIMD operations.
7496 case Kind::kI64x2Add:
7497 case Kind::kI32x4Add:
7498 case Kind::kI16x8Add:
7499 case Kind::kI8x16Add:
7500 case Kind::kF64x2Add:
7501 case Kind::kF32x4Add:
7502
7503 case Kind::kI64x2Mul:
7504 case Kind::kI32x4Mul:
7505 case Kind::kI16x8Mul:
7506 case Kind::kF64x2Mul:
7507 case Kind::kF32x4Mul:
7508 return true;
7509 default:
7510 return false;
7511 }
7512 }
7513
7514 static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects();
7515
7516 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
7517 return RepVector<RegisterRepresentation::Simd128()>();
7518 }
7519
7520 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
7521 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
7522 return MaybeRepVector<RegisterRepresentation::Simd128(),
7523 RegisterRepresentation::Simd128()>();
7524 }
7525
7526 Simd128BinopOp(V<Simd128> left, V<Simd128> right, Kind kind)
7527 : Base(left, right), kind(kind) {}
7528
7529 V<Simd128> left() const { return input<Simd128>(0); }
7530 V<Simd128> right() const { return input<Simd128>(1); }
7531
7532
7533 auto options() const { return std::tuple{kind}; }
7534};
7535V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os,
7536 Simd128BinopOp::Kind kind);

8063
8064// If `mode` is `kLoad`, load a value from `base() + index() + offset`, whose
8065// size is determinded by `lane_kind`, and return the Simd128 `value()` with
8066// the lane specified by `lane_kind` and `lane` replaced with the loaded value.
8067// If `mode` is `kStore`, extract the lane specified by `lane` with size
8068// `lane_kind` from `value()`, and store it to `base() + index() + offset`.
8069struct Simd128LaneMemoryOp : FixedArityOperationT<3, Simd128LaneMemoryOp> {
8070 enum class Mode : bool { kLoad, kStore };
8071 using Kind = LoadOp::Kind;
8072 // The values encode the element_size_log2.
8073 enum class LaneKind : uint8_t { k8 = 0, k16 = 1, k32 = 2, k64 = 3 };
8074
8075 Mode mode;
8076 Kind kind;
8077 LaneKind lane_kind;
8078 uint8_t lane;
8079 int offset;
8080
8081 OpEffects Effects() const {
8082 OpEffects effects = mode == Mode::kLoad ? OpEffects().CanReadMemory()
8083 : OpEffects().CanWriteMemory();
8084 effects = effects.CanDependOnChecks();
8085 if (kind.with_trap_handler) effects = effects.CanLeaveCurrentFunction();
8086 return effects;
8087 }
8088
8089 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
8090 return mode == Mode::kLoad ? RepVector<RegisterRepresentation::Simd128()>()
8091 : RepVector<>();
8092 }
8093
8094 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
8095 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
8096 return MaybeRepVector<RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr(),
8097 RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr(),
8098 RegisterRepresentation::Simd128()>();
8099 }
8100
8101 Simd128LaneMemoryOp(OpIndex base, OpIndex index, OpIndex value, Mode mode,
8102 Kind kind, LaneKind lane_kind, uint8_t lane, int offset)
8103 : Base(base, index, value),
8104 mode(mode),
8105 kind(kind),
8106 lane_kind(lane_kind),
8107 lane(lane),
8108 offset(offset) {}
8109
8110 OpIndex base() const { return input(0); }
8111 OpIndex index() const { return input(1); }
8112 OpIndex value() const { return input(2); }
8113 uint8_t lane_size() const { return 1 << static_cast<uint8_t>(lane_kind); }
8114
8115 void Validate(const Graph& graph) {
8116 DCHECK(!kind.tagged_base);
8117#if DEBUG
8118 uint8_t lane_count;
8119 switch (lane_kind) {
8120 case LaneKind::k8:
8121 lane_count = 16;
8122 break;
8123 case LaneKind::k16:
8124 lane_count = 8;
8125 break;
8126 case LaneKind::k32:
8127 lane_count = 4;
8128 break;
8129 case LaneKind::k64:
8130 lane_count = 2;
8131 break;
8132 }
8133 DCHECK_LT(lane, lane_count);
8134#endif
8135 }
8136
8137 auto options() const {
8138 return std::tuple{mode, kind, lane_kind, lane, offset};
8139 }
8140 void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;
8141};
8142
8143#define FOREACH_SIMD_128_LOAD_TRANSFORM_OPCODE(V) \
8144 V(8x8S) \
8145 V(8x8U) \
8146 V(16x4S) \
8147 V(16x4U) \
8148 V(32x2S) \
8149 V(32x2U) \
8150 V(8Splat) \
8151 V(16Splat) \
8152 V(32Splat) \
8153 V(64Splat) \
8154 V(32Zero) \
8155 V(64Zero)
8156
8157// Load a value from `base() + index() + offset`, whose size is determinded by
8158// `transform_kind`, and generate a Simd128 value as follows:
8159// - From 8x8S to 32x2U (extend kinds), the loaded value has size 8. It is
8160// interpreted as a vector of values according to the size of the kind, which
8161// populate the even lanes of the generated value. The odd lanes are zero- or
8162// sign-extended according to the kind.
8163// - For splat kinds, the loaded value's size is determined by the kind, all
8164// lanes of the generated value are populated with the loaded value.
8165// - For "zero" kinds, the loaded value's size is determined by the kind, and
8166// the generated value zero-extends the loaded value.
8167struct Simd128LoadTransformOp
8168 : FixedArityOperationT<2, Simd128LoadTransformOp> {
8169 using LoadKind = LoadOp::Kind;
8170 enum class TransformKind : uint8_t {
8171#define DEFINE_KIND(kind) k##kind,
8172 FOREACH_SIMD_128_LOAD_TRANSFORM_OPCODE(DEFINE_KIND)
8173#undef DEFINE_KIND
8174 };
8175
8176 LoadKind load_kind;
8177 TransformKind transform_kind;
8178 int offset;
8179
8180 OpEffects Effects() const {
8181 OpEffects effects = OpEffects().CanReadMemory().CanDependOnChecks();
8182 if (load_kind.with_trap_handler) {
8183 effects = effects.CanLeaveCurrentFunction();
8184 }
8185 return effects;
8186 }
8187
8188 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
8189 return RepVector<RegisterRepresentation::Simd128()>();
8190 }
8191
8192 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
8193 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
8194 return MaybeRepVector<RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr(),
8195 RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr()>();
8196 }
8197
8198 Simd128LoadTransformOp(V<WordPtr> base, V<WordPtr> index, LoadKind load_kind,
8199 TransformKind transform_kind, int offset)
8200 : Base(base, index),
8201 load_kind(load_kind),
8202 transform_kind(transform_kind),
8203 offset(offset) {}
8204
8205 V<WordPtr> base() const { return input<WordPtr>(0); }
8206 V<WordPtr> index() const { return input<WordPtr>(1); }
8207
8208 void Validate(const Graph& graph) { DCHECK(!load_kind.tagged_base); }
8209
8210 auto options() const { return std::tuple{load_kind, transform_kind, offset}; }
8211 void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;
8212};
8213
8214// Takes two Simd128 inputs and generates a Simd128 value. The 8-bit lanes of
8215// both inputs are numbered 0-31, and each output 8-bit lane is selected from
8216// among the input lanes according to `shuffle`.
8217struct Simd128ShuffleOp : FixedArityOperationT<2, Simd128ShuffleOp> {
8218 uint8_t shuffle[kSimd128Size];
8219
8220 static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects();
8221
8222 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
8223 return RepVector<RegisterRepresentation::Simd128()>();
8224 }
8225
8226 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
8227 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
8228 return MaybeRepVector<RegisterRepresentation::Simd128(),
8229 RegisterRepresentation::Simd128()>();
8230 }
8231
8232 Simd128ShuffleOp(V<Simd128> left, V<Simd128> right,
8233 const uint8_t incoming_shuffle[kSimd128Size])
8234 : Base(left, right) {
8235 std::copy(incoming_shuffle, incoming_shuffle + kSimd128Size, shuffle);
8236 }
8237
8238 V<Simd128> left() const { return input<Simd128>(0); }
8239 V<Simd128> right() const { return input<Simd128>(1); }
8240
8241 void Validate(const Graph& graph) {
8242#if DEBUG
8243 constexpr uint8_t kNumberOfLanesForShuffle = 32;
8244 for (uint8_t index : shuffle) {
8245 DCHECK_LT(index, kNumberOfLanesForShuffle);
8246 }
8247#endif
8248 }
8249
8250 auto options() const { return std::tuple{shuffle}; }
8251 void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;
8252};

8309 }
8310
8311 auto options() const { return std::tuple{lane}; }
8312 void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;
8313};

8328struct Simd256LoadTransformOp
8329 : FixedArityOperationT<2, Simd256LoadTransformOp> {
8330 using LoadKind = LoadOp::Kind;
8331 enum class TransformKind : uint8_t {
8332#define DEFINE_KIND(kind) k##kind,
8333 FOREACH_SIMD_256_LOAD_TRANSFORM_OPCODE(DEFINE_KIND)
8334#undef DEFINE_KIND
8335 };
8336
8337 LoadKind load_kind;
8338 TransformKind transform_kind;
8339 int offset;
8340
8341 OpEffects Effects() const {
8342 OpEffects effects = OpEffects().CanReadMemory().CanDependOnChecks();
8343 if (load_kind.with_trap_handler) {
8344 effects = effects.CanLeaveCurrentFunction();
8345 }
8346 return effects;
8347 }
8348
8349 base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
8350 return RepVector<RegisterRepresentation::Simd256()>();
8351 }
8352
8353 base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
8354 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
8355 return MaybeRepVector<RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr(),
8356 RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr()>();
8357 }
8358
8359 Simd256LoadTransformOp(V<WordPtr> base, V<WordPtr> index, LoadKind load_kind,
8360 TransformKind transform_kind, int offset)
8361 : Base(base, index),
8362 load_kind(load_kind),
8363 transform_kind(transform_kind),
8364 offset(offset) {}
8365
8366 V<WordPtr> base() const { return input<WordPtr>(0); }
8367 V<WordPtr> index() const { return input<WordPtr>(1); }
8368
8369 void Validate(const Graph& graph) { DCHECK(!load_kind.tagged_base); }
8370
8371 auto options() const { return std::tuple{load_kind, transform_kind, offset}; }
8372 void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;
8373};

8923template <class Op>
8924const Opcode OperationT<Op>::opcode = operation_to_opcode<Op>::value;
8925
8926template <Opcode opcode>
8927struct opcode_to_operation_map {};
8928
8929#define OPERATION_OPCODE_MAP_CASE(Name) \
8930 template <> \
8931 struct opcode_to_operation_map<Opcode::k##Name> { \
8932 using Op = Name##Op; \
8933 };
8934TURBOSHAFT_OPERATION_LIST(OPERATION_OPCODE_MAP_CASE)
8935#undef OPERATION_OPCODE_MAP_CASE
8936
8937template <class Op, class = void>
8938struct static_operation_input_count : std::integral_constant<uint32_t, 0> {};
8939template <class Op>
8940struct static_operation_input_count<Op, std::void_t<decltype(Op::inputs)>>
8941 : std::integral_constant<uint32_t, sizeof(Op::inputs) / sizeof(OpIndex)> {};
8942constexpr size_t kOperationSizeTable[kNumberOfOpcodes] = {
8943#define OPERATION_SIZE(Name) sizeof(Name##Op),
8944 TURBOSHAFT_OPERATION_LIST(OPERATION_SIZE)
8945#undef OPERATION_SIZE
8946};
8947constexpr size_t kOperationSizeDividedBySizeofOpIndexTable[kNumberOfOpcodes] = {
8948#define OPERATION_SIZE(Name) (sizeof(Name##Op) / sizeof(OpIndex)),
8949 TURBOSHAFT_OPERATION_LIST(OPERATION_SIZE)
8950#undef OPERATION_SIZE
8951};
8952
8953inline base::Vector<const OpIndex> Operation::inputs() const {
8954 // This is actually undefined behavior, since we use the `this` pointer to
8955 // access an adjacent object.
8956 const OpIndex* ptr = reinterpret_cast<const OpIndex*>(
8957 reinterpret_cast<const char*>(this) +
8958 kOperationSizeTable[OpcodeIndex(opcode)]);
8959 return {ptr, input_count};
8960}
8961
8962inline OpEffects Operation::Effects() const {
8963 if (auto prop = kOperationEffectsTable[OpcodeIndex(opcode)]) {
8964 return *prop;
8965 }
8966 switch (opcode) {
8967 case Opcode::kLoad:
8968 return Cast<LoadOp>().Effects();
8969 case Opcode::kStore:
8970 return Cast<StoreOp>().Effects();
8971 case Opcode::kCall:
8972 return Cast<CallOp>().Effects();
8973 case Opcode::kDidntThrow:
8974 return Cast<DidntThrowOp>().Effects();
8975 case Opcode::kTaggedBitcast:
8976 return Cast<TaggedBitcastOp>().Effects();
8977 case Opcode::kAtomicRMW:
8978 return Cast<AtomicRMWOp>().Effects();
8979 case Opcode::kAtomicWord32Pair:
8980 return Cast<AtomicWord32PairOp>().Effects();
8981 case Opcode::kJSStackCheck:
8982 return Cast<JSStackCheckOp>().Effects();
8983#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
8984 case Opcode::kWasmStackCheck:
8985 return Cast<WasmStackCheckOp>().Effects();
8986 case Opcode::kStructGet:
8987 return Cast<StructGetOp>().Effects();
8988 case Opcode::kStructSet:
8989 return Cast<StructSetOp>().Effects();
8990 case Opcode::kArrayLength:
8991 return Cast<ArrayLengthOp>().Effects();
8992 case Opcode::kSimd128LaneMemory:
8993 return Cast<Simd128LaneMemoryOp>().Effects();
8994 case Opcode::kSimd128LoadTransform:
8995 return Cast<Simd128LoadTransformOp>().Effects();
8996#if V8_ENABLE_WASM_SIMD256_REVEC
8997 case Opcode::kSimd256LoadTransform:
8998 return Cast<Simd256LoadTransformOp>().Effects();
8999#endif // V8_ENABLE_WASM_SIMD256_REVEC
9000#endif
9001 default:
9002 UNREACHABLE();
9003 }
9004}
9005
9006// static
9007inline size_t Operation::StorageSlotCount(Opcode opcode, size_t input_count) {
9008 size_t size = kOperationSizeDividedBySizeofOpIndexTable[OpcodeIndex(opcode)];
9009 constexpr size_t r = sizeof(OperationStorageSlot) / sizeof(OpIndex);
9010 static_assert(sizeof(OperationStorageSlot) % sizeof(OpIndex) == 0);
9011 return std::max<size_t>(2, (r - 1 + size + input_count) / r);
9012}
9013
9014V8_INLINE bool CanBeUsedAsInput(const Operation& op) {
9015 return op.Is<FrameStateOp>() || op.outputs_rep().size() > 0;
9016}
9017
9018inline base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> Operation::outputs_rep()
9019 const {
9020 switch (opcode) {
9021#define CASE(type) \
9022 case Opcode::k##type: { \
9023 const type##Op& op = Cast<type##Op>(); \
9024 return op.outputs_rep(); \
9025 }
9026 TURBOSHAFT_OPERATION_LIST(CASE)
9027#undef CASE
9028 }
9029}
9030
9031inline base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> Operation::inputs_rep(
9032 ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
9033 switch (opcode) {
9034#define CASE(type) \
9035 case Opcode::k##type: { \
9036 const type##Op& op = Cast<type##Op>(); \
9037 return op.inputs_rep(storage); \
9038 }
9039 TURBOSHAFT_OPERATION_LIST(CASE)
9040#undef CASE
9041 }
9042}
9043
9044bool IsUnlikelySuccessor(const Block* block, const Block* successor,
9045 const Graph& graph);
9046
9047// Analyzers should skip (= ignore) operations for which ShouldSkipOperation
9048// returns true. This happens for:
9049// - DeadOp: this means that a previous Analyzer decided that this operation is
9050// dead.
9051// - Operations that are not RequiredWhenUnused, and whose saturated_use_count
9052// is 0: this corresponds to pure operations that have no uses.
9053V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE V8_INLINE bool ShouldSkipOperation(const Operation& op) {
9054 if (op.Is<DeadOp>()) return true;
9055 return op.saturated_use_count.IsZero() && !op.IsRequiredWhenUnused();
9056}
9057
9058namespace detail {
9059// Defining `input_count` to compute the number of OpIndex inputs of an
9060// operation.
9061
9062// There is one overload for each possible type of parameters for all
9063// Operations rather than a default generic overload, so that we don't
9064// accidentally forget some types (eg, if a new Operation takes its inputs as a
9065// std::vector<OpIndex>, we shouldn't count this as "0 inputs because it's
9066// neither raw OpIndex nor base::Vector<OpIndex>", which a generic overload
9067// might do).
9068
9069// Base case
9070constexpr size_t input_count() { return 0; }
9071
9072// All parameters that are not OpIndex and should thus not count towards the
9073// "input_count" of the operations.
9074template <typename T>
9075constexpr size_t input_count(T)
9076 requires(std::is_enum_v<T> || std::is_integral_v<T> ||
9077 std::is_floating_point_v<T>)
9078{
9079 return 0;
9080}
9081// TODO(42203211): The first parameter should be just DirectHandle<T> and
9082// MaybeDirectHandle<T> but now it does not compile with implicit Handle to
9083// DirectHandle conversions.
9084template <template <typename> typename HandleType, typename T>
9085constexpr size_t input_count(const HandleType<T>)
9086 requires(std::disjunction_v<
9087 std::is_convertible<HandleType<T>, DirectHandle<T>>,
9088 std::is_convertible<HandleType<T>, MaybeDirectHandle<T>>>)
9089{
9090 return 0;
9091}
9092template <typename T>
9093constexpr size_t input_count(const base::Flags<T>) {
9094 return 0;
9095}
9096constexpr size_t input_count(const Block*) { return 0; }
9097constexpr size_t input_count(const TSCallDescriptor*) { return 0; }
9098constexpr size_t input_count(const char*) { return 0; }
9099constexpr size_t input_count(const DeoptimizeParameters*) { return 0; }
9100constexpr size_t input_count(const FastApiCallParameters*) { return 0; }
9101constexpr size_t input_count(const FrameStateData*) { return 0; }
9102constexpr size_t input_count(const base::Vector<SwitchOp::Case>) { return 0; }
9103constexpr size_t input_count(LoadOp::Kind) { return 0; }
9104constexpr size_t input_count(RegisterRepresentation) { return 0; }
9105constexpr size_t input_count(MemoryRepresentation) { return 0; }
9106constexpr size_t input_count(OpEffects) { return 0; }
9107constexpr size_t input_count(ExternalPointerTagRange) { return 0; }
9108inline size_t input_count(const ElementsTransition) { return 0; }
9109inline size_t input_count(const ElementsTransitionWithMultipleSources) {
9110 return 0;
9111}
9112inline size_t input_count(const FeedbackSource) { return 0; }
9113inline size_t input_count(const ZoneRefSet<Map>) { return 0; }
9114inline size_t input_count(ConstantOp::Storage) { return 0; }
9115inline size_t input_count(Type) { return 0; }
9116inline size_t input_count(base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation>) {
9117 return 0;
9118}
9119#ifdef V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
9120constexpr size_t input_count(const wasm::WasmGlobal*) { return 0; }
9121constexpr size_t input_count(const wasm::StructType*) { return 0; }
9122constexpr size_t input_count(const wasm::ArrayType*) { return 0; }
9123constexpr size_t input_count(wasm::ValueType) { return 0; }
9124constexpr size_t input_count(WasmTypeCheckConfig) { return 0; }
9125constexpr size_t input_count(wasm::ModuleTypeIndex) { return 0; }
9126#endif
9127
9128// All parameters that are OpIndex-like (ie, OpIndex, and OpIndex containers)
9129constexpr size_t input_count(OpIndex) { return 1; }
9130constexpr size_t input_count(OptionalOpIndex) { return 1; }
9131constexpr size_t input_count(base::Vector<const OpIndex> inputs) {
9132 return inputs.size();
9133}
9134template <typename T>
9135constexpr size_t input_count(base::Vector<const V<T>> inputs) {
9136 return inputs.size();
9137}
9138} // namespace detail
9139
9140template <typename Op, typename... Args>
9141Op* CreateOperation(base::SmallVector<OperationStorageSlot, 32>& storage,
9142 Args... args) {
9143 size_t input_count = (0 + ... + detail::input_count(args));
9144 size_t size = Operation::StorageSlotCount(Op::opcode, input_count);
9145 storage.resize_no_init(size);
9146 Op* op = new (storage.data()) Op(args...);
9147 // Checking that the {input_count} we computed is at least the actual
9148 // input_count of the operation. {input_count} could be greater in the case of
9149 // OptionalOpIndex: they count for 1 input when computing {input_count} here,
9150 // but in Operations, they only count for 1 input when they are valid.
9151 DCHECK_GE(input_count, op->input_count);
9152 return op;
9153}
9154
9155template <typename F>
9156auto VisitOperation(const Operation& op, F&& f) {
9157 switch (op.opcode) {
9158#define CASE(name) \
9159 case Opcode::k##name: \
9160 return f(op.Cast<name##Op>());
9161 TURBOSHAFT_OPERATION_LIST(CASE)
9162#undef CASE
9163 }
9164}
9165
9166// Checking that throwing operations have the required members and options.
9167namespace details {
9168
9169template <typename T, typename Tuple>
9170struct TupleHasType;
9171
9172template <typename T, typename... Ts>
9173struct TupleHasType<T, std::tuple<Ts...>> {
9174 static constexpr bool value = (std::is_same_v<T, Ts> || ...);
9175};
9176
9177template <typename Op, typename = void>
9178struct ThrowingOpHasProperMembers : std::false_type {};
9179template <typename Op>
9180struct ThrowingOpHasProperMembers<
9181 Op, std::void_t<std::conjunction<decltype(Op::kOutputRepsStorage),
9182 decltype(Op::lazy_deopt_on_throw)>>>
9183 : std::true_type {};
9184
9185template <typename Op, typename = void>
9186struct ThrowingOpHasLazyDeoptOption : std::false_type {};
9187
9188template <typename Op>
9189struct ThrowingOpHasLazyDeoptOption<
9190 Op, std::enable_if_t<TupleHasType<
9191 LazyDeoptOnThrow, decltype(std::declval<Op>().options())>::value>>
9192 : std::true_type {};
9193
9194// CallOp has special handling because its outputs_rep are dynamic (and found on
9195// its call descriptor).
9196template <>
9197struct ThrowingOpHasLazyDeoptOption<CallOp, void> : std::true_type {};
9198template <>
9199struct ThrowingOpHasProperMembers<CallOp, void> : std::true_type {};
9200
9201template <>
9202struct ThrowingOpHasProperMembers<FastApiCallOp, void> : std::true_type {};
9203} // namespace details
9204
9205#define THROWING_OP_LOOKS_VALID(Name) \
9206 static_assert(details::ThrowingOpHasProperMembers<Name##Op>()); \
9207 static_assert(details::ThrowingOpHasLazyDeoptOption<Name##Op>());
9208TURBOSHAFT_THROWING_OPERATIONS_LIST(THROWING_OP_LOOKS_VALID)
9209#undef THROWING_OP_LOOKS_VALID
9210
9211} // namespace v8::internal::compiler::turboshaft
